:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"how to optimize images in wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Image SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"optimize images for web\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"seo image optimization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"what is image seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=31215\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:552:\"<p>Do you want to know how to optimize your images in WordPress and get more organic traffic from image search? Every day more than 1 billion searches are made on Google Images. That’s why we decided to create a list of 17 tips on how to best optimize your images in WordPress to improve rankings and drive more traffic to your website.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-best-optimize-images-in-wordpress/\">Image SEO: How To Best Optimize Your Images In WordPress (18 Tips)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40589:\"<p>Do you want to know how to optimize images in WordPress and get more organic traffic from image search?&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every day more than 1 billion searches are made on Google Images, making them a great opportunity to help you rank and gain more visibility in search. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why we decided to create a list of tips on how to best optimize your images in WordPress to improve rankings and drive more traffic to your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Since this is a comprehensive list, you can click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-image-seo\">What Is Image SEO?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-should-you-use-images-in-your-content\">Why Should You Use Images in Your Content?</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-optimize-your-images-in-wordpress\">How to Optimize Your Images in WordPress</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-1-use-the-right-image-seo-tool\">1. Use the Right Image SEO Tool</a></li><li><a href=\"#use-descriptive-image-file-names\">2. Use Descriptive Image File Names</a></li><li><a href=\"#write-seo-friendly-alt-text\">3. Write SEO-Friendly Alt Text</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor\">Adding Alt Text in WordPress Block Editor</a></li><li><a href=\"#use-image-caption-when-needed\">4. Use Image Caption When Needed</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-adding-image-captions-in-wordpress-block-editor\">Adding Image Captions in WordPress Block Editor</a></li><li><a href=\"#consider-your-seo-title-and-description\">5. Consider Your SEO Title and Description</a></li><li><a href=\"#disable-attachment-pages\">6. Disable Attachment Pages</a></li><li><a href=\"#define-your-image-dimensions\">7. Define Your Image Dimensions</a></li><li><a href=\"#choose-the-right-image-format\">8. Choose the Right Image Format</a></li><li><a href=\"#create-an-image-sitemap\">9. Create an Image Sitemap</a></li><li><a href=\"#use-structured-data-to-rank-for-rich-snippets\">10. Use Image Structured Data to Rank for Rich Snippets</a></li><li><a href=\"#add-facebook-thumbnails-and-twitter-cards\">11. Add Facebook Thumbnails and Twitter Cards</a></li><li><a href=\"#compress-your-images-to-reduce-file-size\">12. Compress Your Images to Reduce File Size</a></li><li><a href=\"#lazy-load-your-images\">13. Lazy Load Your Images</a></li><li><a href=\"#use-responsive-images\">14. Use Responsive Images</a></li><li><a href=\"#install-a-cache-plugin\">15. Install a Cache Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#serve-your-images-via-an-image-cdn\">16. Serve Your images Via an Image CDN</a></li><li><a href=\"#make-your-website-mobile-friendly\">17. Make Your Website Mobile-Friendly</a></li><li><a href=\"#prepare-for-google-lens-visual-search\">18. Prepare for Google Lens Visual Search</a></li></ul></li></ul></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-image-seo\">What Is Image SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Image SEO, also called image optimization, is the process of optimizing the images on your website to make it easy for Google to find and rank your images.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, it helps Google and other search engines to understand your content and show your images in the image search results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And to make this happen, you&#8217;ve to optimize your images for the web, which we’ll show you how to do. But first, let’s take a look at why you should use images in your content, to begin with.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-why-should-you-use-images-in-your-content\">Why Should You Use Images in Your Content?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>First things first: Why should you use images in your content?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You should use images because they add value to your content and grab people&#8217;s attention.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If used properly, images can spike people’s interest and make them click through to your site, increasing your rankings in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, image search represents about 20.45% of all searches on Google and other popular sites.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"411\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-engine-market-share-by-sparktoro.png\" alt=\"Search engine market share infographic by SparkToro\" class=\"wp-image-31216\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-engine-market-share-by-sparktoro.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-engine-market-share-by-sparktoro-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-engine-market-share-by-sparktoro-704x396.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-engine-market-share-by-sparktoro-600x338.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This should make you realize why adding images to your content and optimizing them for SEO is a good idea.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you need to think about is whether your images are relevant to the topic of your page. More importantly, if they&#8217;re adding value to your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, you should place the most important image on top of your page and try using original photographs that are unique to your blog or website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But there’s more to it than that&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;there are more things you need to do if you want to be featured in Google’s image search and improve your rankings, and that’s what we’ll show you next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-optimize-your-images-in-wordpress\">How to Optimize Your Images in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To optimize your images in WordPress, you’ve to make sure you add additional information about your images, so search engines can understand what they’re about.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engines are getting smarter every day. They can recognize and categorize images quite well. But they need you to provide context to the image and optimize your images to rank for image search.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-1-use-the-right-image-seo-tool\">1. Use the Right Image SEO Tool</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first steps to ensuring you nail your image SEO is to use the right image SEO tool.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And it doesn’t get better than <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best SEO image SEO plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is a powerful WordPress SEO plugin trusted by over 3 million websites. Savvy marketers use it to help drive traffic and rank high on SERPs. With AIOSEO, you get access to all the advanced SEO tools you’ll need to take your SEO efforts to the next level without having to be an SEO expert.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the plugin&#8217;s most loved features is the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/image-seo/\" title=\"Image SEO\">Image SEO module</a>. This is a powerful module that makes optimizing your images way easier. For example, you can optimize your image metadata by:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Setting a format (similar to the SEO title/description formats)</li><li>Stripping punctuation</li><li>Converting the casing</li><li>And more </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>To use this feature, go to your <strong>AIOSEO dashboard » Search Appearance » Image SEO</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"491\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image-seo-1-min.png\" alt=\"You can then optimize your image\'s metadata by clicking on the relevant tab, that is, Title, Alt Tag, Caption, Description, or Filename.\" class=\"wp-image-114767\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image-seo-1-min.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image-seo-1-min-300x210.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image-seo-1-min-600x420.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can then optimize the image metadata by clicking on the relevant tab (Title, Alt Tag, Caption, Description, or Filename). You can also choose the pages you want to implement these optimizations on:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"402\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image-seo-2.png\" alt=\"You can choose which pages to implement the metadata optimizations on.\" class=\"wp-image-114771\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image-seo-2.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image-seo-2-300x172.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/image-seo-2-600x345.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your images this way makes it easier for search engines to understand what your image is about as it helps add context. It also enhances the user experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out this <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">installation guide</a> for detailed instructions on installing AIOSEO on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"use-descriptive-image-file-names\">2. Use Descriptive Image File Names</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You should always name your images with as descriptive file names as possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s what Google says about image filenames:</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;[…] the filename can give Google clues about the subject matter of the image. For example, my-new-black-kitten.jpg is better than IMG00023.jpg.&#8221;</p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>To give you another example, here’s a photo of a playful black kitten. Instead of naming it IMG00021.jpg, we’ve named it playful-black-kitten.jpg, which is a better description of the image.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"466\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-descriptive-image-file-name.png\" alt=\"Image SEO: How to best optimize your images in WordPress - use descriptive file names\" class=\"wp-image-31217\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-descriptive-image-file-name.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-descriptive-image-file-name-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-descriptive-image-file-name-600x383.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Try to be specific. For instance, big-eyed-playful-black-kitten.jpg is better than just black-kitten.jpg.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, consider the keywords that users would type on Google to find your image.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"write-seo-friendly-alt-text\">3. Write SEO-Friendly Alt Text</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Alt text or alternative text is crucial for image SEO. It helps Google understand what the image is about. It’s an HTML attribute added to the image tag, which is used to show images on a page.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It can look like this in plain HTML code:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;img src=\"img_playful-black-kitten.jpg\" alt=\"Playful black kitten\" width=\"500\" height=\"600\"&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned, the alt text is used to describe your image. And if your image can’t be displayed, users can still understand what the image is about by reading the text.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s good for people who use screen readers or have low bandwidth connections. Alt texts are also useful as anchor texts if you’re linking images.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t just use one or two words to write your alt text. Instead, imagine how you would describe your image to a blind person.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, instead of just ‘chocolate,’ use ‘dark chocolate banana bread muffins’. This will also help Google to rank your image since it uses a combination of alt texts, computer vision algorithms, and the contents of your page to understand what your image is about.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But don’t stuff your alt text with different keywords thinking it’ll help you rank better in image search. In fact, it can result in the opposite, and Google may see your site as spam.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor\">Adding Alt Text in WordPress Block Editor</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To add alt text to your images is super easy when using the WordPress block editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply scroll down in the post or page you’re editing and click on your image so that it gets marked with the blue frame. Then, go to the <strong>Image Settings</strong> in the right column of your editor and type in your alt text in the<strong> Alt Text (alternative text) </strong>field.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"367\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor.png\" alt=\"Adding alt text in WordPress block editor \" class=\"wp-image-31218\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor-300x151.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor-600x302.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Alt texts aren’t visible on your site, while captions are shown below your images, which we’ll look at next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"use-image-caption-when-needed\">4. Use Image Caption When Needed</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Image captions make your content scannable. People tend to scan headings, images, and captions when they’re quickly eying through a page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, they can make your content look cluttered and aren’t really necessary since you’re explaining the image in the content itself.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Still, captions can be good for:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Family or event photos</li><li>Photos that need additional explanation describing a background story</li><li>And product image galleries</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-adding-image-captions-in-wordpress-block-editor\">Adding Image Captions in WordPress Block Editor</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To add your image caption in the WordPress block editor, you simply scroll down in the post or page you’re editing and click on your image, so it gets marked with the blue frame. Next, enter your image caption in the <strong>Caption</strong> field below the image, and it’s added!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"382\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/adding-image-caption-in-block-editor.png\" alt=\"Adding image captions in WordPress block editor\" class=\"wp-image-37097\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/adding-image-caption-in-block-editor.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/adding-image-caption-in-block-editor-300x157.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/adding-image-caption-in-block-editor-600x314.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/adding-image-caption-in-block-editor-115x60.png 115w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/adding-image-caption-in-block-editor-172x90.png 172w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"consider-your-seo-title-and-description\">5. Consider Your SEO Title and Description</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Google also uses your page’s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-title-tags/\" title=\"How to Write Great SEO Title Tags for Search Engines and People\">SEO title</a> and description when deciding what description to show below your image in the search results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s what Google says:</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&#8220;Google Images automatically generates a title and snippet to best explain each result and how it relates to the user query… We use a number of different sources for this information, including descriptive information in the title, and meta tags.&#8221;</p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>To better illustrate this, here’s an example of the image search results on Google for ‘tasty chocolate muffins‘:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/alt-text-in-image-search-on-google.png\" alt=\"Example of image search on Google\" class=\"wp-image-31219\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/alt-text-in-image-search-on-google.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/alt-text-in-image-search-on-google-300x198.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/alt-text-in-image-search-on-google-600x396.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, all images have descriptions below them. And Google uses your page’s SEO title and description to generate these.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why your images have to relate to your title and description. If you want to know how to easily edit your SEO title, please check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-change-the-seo-title-in-wordpress\">how to change the SEO title in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"disable-attachment-pages\">6. Disable Attachment Pages</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress creates a page for all images you upload to your posts and pages. It’s called an attachment page.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The only thing this page does is to show a larger version of your mage, which in fact, can hurt your SEO. Search engines consider pages with little to no text as low-quality or ‘thin content.&#8217;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fortunately, it’s easy to disable the attachment pages on your WordPress site. And the easiest way to do this is by installing and activating the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress/\" title=\"8 Best SEO Plugins for WordPress in 2022 (Tried and Tested)\">best WordPress SEO plugin</a> in the market, All in One SEO (AIOSEO).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Disabling image attachment pages is also a great way to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-delete-url-parameters-from-google-search-console/\" title=\"How to Delete URL Parameters from Google Search Console (The Easy Way)\">eliminate unnecessary URL parameters</a> on your site. Eliminating these is an excellent way of increasing crawl efficiency on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you’ve activated AIOSEO, it automatically turns off attachment URLs. You can also manually turn them off by visiting <strong>All in One SEO » Search Appearance</strong> and clicking on the <strong>Media</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"256\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/attachement-urls-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Image SEO: How to best optimize your images in WordPress - disable attachment pages\" class=\"wp-image-31222\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/attachement-urls-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/attachement-urls-in-all-in-one-seo-300x105.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/attachement-urls-in-all-in-one-seo-600x210.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure that the <strong>Redirect Attachment URLs</strong> option is set to <strong>Attachment</strong>, and that’s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"define-your-image-dimensions\">7. Define Your Image Dimensions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You should resize your images to fit the blog content of your page. Even if your website fills up the whole width of the screen, the blog section has a set maximum width. And using larger images will slow down your page loading and negatively affect your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if your blog’s maximum width is 706px, your images will never be displayed wider than 706px.&nbsp;And if you have a responsive website, the browser will resize images that are wider than 706px to fit them on the screen.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At least this makes your site look good, right?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, there&#8217;s one problem&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;when using large images, the browser still has to load your image in its full size. Even worse, large images are heavy in file size and will reduce your page loading speed. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why you should resize and upload your images to the maximum width of your blog or page.&nbsp;Fortunately, it&#8217;s easy to check this.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, go to the <strong>Web Developer</strong> settings in your browser and click on the <strong>Inspector </strong>tool. Then, you simply hover over the column you want to check, and a black box with the dimensions will appear.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"553\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/checking-your-blog-width.png\" alt=\"Image SEO: How to best optimize your images in WordPress - check blog content width\" class=\"wp-image-31223\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/checking-your-blog-width.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/checking-your-blog-width-300x227.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/checking-your-blog-width-600x455.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, AIOSEO’s blog width is 706px, which is the maximum width our images should be uploaded in <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/10-quick-easy-ways-to-speed-up-your-site/\" title=\"10 Ways to Speed up Your WordPress Site\">not to slow down our page loading</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"choose-the-right-image-format\">8. Choose the Right Image Format&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As we just explained, images often make your website big in file size and too heavy. Your site won’t load fast enough for visitors to wait around for it.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Instead, they’ll choose another site that’s loading faster, and you’ll lose out on traffic and potential customers. This will also hurt your rankings in search engines since your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-reduce-bounce-rate/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">bounce rate</a> will increase.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Depending on what image format you use, your image file size will be larger or smaller. It’ll also impact the quality of your images.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The most common image file types are JPG, PNG, and GIF. Each of them serves its purpose depending on what images you’re creating or uploading to your site:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>JPG is best for website graphics that have many shades of colors </li><li>PNG is best when you want top-quality and size isn’t an issue</li><li>GIF is for animations or moving images</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>JPGs are generally smaller in file size than PNG’s and GIFs. However, PNG is better for high-quality images, such as screenshots, drawings, and images with text where you need to keep the image quality.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"create-an-image-sitemap\">9. Create an Image Sitemap</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can help Google index and crawl your images faster by creating an image sitemap. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>When using AIOSEO, creating an XML image sitemap is as easy as a walk in the park. In fact, all images on your website are automatically included in the XML sitemap. And this function is what’s called an Image Sitemap.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All you need to do is activate AIOSEO, and it automatically creates a sitemap for you. You can check so that it’s enabled by navigating to <strong>Sitemaps</strong> in the <strong>All in One SEO </strong>menu and clicking on the <strong>General Sitemap</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"General sitemap settings in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31227\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-600x353.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open the General Sitemap window, where you can see that <strong>Enable Sitemap </strong>is set to on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"346\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Enable sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31228\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As simple as that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to know how to customize your sitemap and exclude certain images or content, you can check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">how to create a sitemap in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, make sure your images aren’t blocked by your robots.txt file. If you don’t want Google to crawl your images, you can disallow them using robots.txt. For more details, please visit our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-edit-a-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress/\">how to easily edit a robots.txt file in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"use-structured-data-to-rank-for-rich-snippets\">10. Use Image Structured Data to Rank for Rich Snippets</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you add schema markup or structured data to your site, Google Images can show your images as rich results with a prominent badge of what your page is about.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example of when Recipe schema markup is added to your site: </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"483\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/prominent-badge-google-image-search.png\" alt=\"Example of prominent badge for Google Images\" class=\"wp-image-31233\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/prominent-badge-google-image-search.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/prominent-badge-google-image-search-300x198.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/prominent-badge-google-image-search-600x397.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, it shows a prominent badge with a fork and knife indicating that it’s a recipe.&nbsp;This gives users more information about your page, which will increase your CTR (Click-Through-Rate) and drive more organic traffic to your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Images supports schema markup for:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Products</li><li>Videos</li><li>Recipes</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily add schema markup to your site and get these nice looking rich results using AIOSEO. To learn how to do this, you can check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-rich-snippets-to-wordpress/\">how to add rich snippets to WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"add-facebook-thumbnails-and-twitter-cards\">11. Add Facebook Thumbnails and Twitter Cards</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way of driving more traffic to your site is by utilizing your social media profiles. And a first step is to make sure the right images are shown when shared on social media.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can optimize your images and control how they look when your content is shared on Twitter and Facebook. You can easily do this by adding Twitter Cards and Facebook thumbnails to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, here’s what one of our posts looks like after choosing which thumbnail’s used when it’s shared on Facebook:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"397\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-facebook-thumbnail-example.png\" alt=\"Example of Facebook thumbnail when your content is shared on Facebook\" class=\"wp-image-24265\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-facebook-thumbnail-example.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-facebook-thumbnail-example-300x163.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-facebook-thumbnail-example-600x326.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And here’s a Twitter Card when <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/convert-plus-vs-optinmonster/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">OptinMonster’s</a> post is shared on Twitter:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"405\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/optinmonster-twitter-card-example-1.png\" alt=\"Example of Twitter Card when your content is shared on Twitter\" class=\"wp-image-23906\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/optinmonster-twitter-card-example-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/optinmonster-twitter-card-example-1-300x166.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/optinmonster-twitter-card-example-1-600x333.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out how to easily set this up by visiting <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress/\">how to fix the wrong Facebook thumbnail </a>and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-twitter-cards-in-wordpress/\">how to add Twitter Cards in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"compress-your-images-to-reduce-file-size\">12. Compress Your Images to Reduce File Size</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/tiny-png-image-compression.png\" alt=\"Compress your images using TinyPNG \" class=\"wp-image-27767\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/tiny-png-image-compression.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/tiny-png-image-compression-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/tiny-png-image-compression-600x296.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned, site speed is crucial for SEO. Google has confirmed that it’s a ranking factor on both desktop and mobile. And this is also true for image search.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Starting May 2021, Google will make website loading speed a part of its Core Web Vitals. These are factors that Google considers important for giving users the best experience when visiting your site. For instance, it’ll look at your site speed, responsiveness, and how quickly different elements like images and fonts load.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step in optimizing your images for site speed is to compress them. And you can use free services, such as:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://tinypng.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">TinyPNG</a> for PNG &amp; JPG files</li><li><a href=\"https://compressjpeg.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">CompressJPEG</a> for JPG files</li><li><a href=\"https://imagecompressor.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Optimizilla</a> for PNG &amp; JPG files</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This can reduce your image file size by 70% or more, positively impacting your site speed.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"lazy-load-your-images\">13. Lazy Load Your Images</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"706\" height=\"262\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-5-4.jpg\" alt=\"WordPress 5.4 lazy loads images by default\" class=\"wp-image-31494\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-5-4.jpg 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-5-4-300x111.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-5-4-704x262.jpg 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-5-4-600x223.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have a lot of images and content on your site, it’s always good to use <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-lazy-load-images-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Lazy Load Images in WordPress (2 Methods)\">lazy loading</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lazy loading shows the images on your page only when they’re visible to the user as they scroll down your content. This makes the communication between your site and the server more efficient, which makes your page load faster.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s what Google says about lazy-loading:</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;Lazy loading can significantly speed up loading on long pages that include many images below the fold by loading them either as needed or when the primary content has finished loading and rendering.&#8221;</p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>Guess what&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;if you&#8217;re using WordPress 5.4 and newer versions, it will lazy load your images by default. So you don&#8217;t have to worry about installing a lazy load plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you want to add lazy loading for other HTML elements such as iframes, videos, and background images, you can use a lazy load plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rocket\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">WP Rocket</a> to speed up your page loading even more. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"use-responsive-images\">14. Use Responsive Images</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Using responsive images lets your site show a larger, higher resolution image on your desktop. It also enables mobile sites to show a zoomed-in image on mobile and makes the image size smaller, increasing a page&#8217;s load speed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re using WordPress, you don’t have to worry about this. WordPress automatically makes your images responsive after uploading them and shows them in different sizes on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, if you want to know how your images affect your site speed, you can test this using Google’s <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/speed/pagespeed/insights/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">PageSpeed Insights</a> tool.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"install-a-cache-plugin\">15. Install a Cache Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rocket/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"372\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wp-rocket-homepage.png\" alt=\"Cache plugin to speed up your website by WP Rocket\" class=\"wp-image-31236\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wp-rocket-homepage.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wp-rocket-homepage-300x153.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wp-rocket-homepage-600x306.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Browser caching can help speed up your website by storing some of the larger files on your site, including images, locally in the user’s web browser.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A cache plugin makes a copy of your page after the first-page load,s and then serves that cached version to other users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rocket/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">WP Rocket</a> offers a comprehensive set of tools to help speed up your website, such as page caching and preloading.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to know more options, you can check out our post on the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-cache-plugin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">best WordPress cache plugins</a> we recommend. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"serve-your-images-via-an-image-cdn\">16. Serve Your images Via an Image CDN</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img width=\"730\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/why-you-need-cdn-for-your-site.png\" alt=\"Serve your images via an image CDN\" class=\"wp-image-37098\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/why-you-need-cdn-for-your-site.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/why-you-need-cdn-for-your-site-300x144.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/why-you-need-cdn-for-your-site-600x288.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/why-you-need-cdn-for-your-site-125x60.png 125w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/why-you-need-cdn-for-your-site-187x90.png 187w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/why-you-need-a-cdn-for-your-wordpress-blog-infographic/?display=wide\"></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to speed up your site, even more, you should use an image CDN (Content Delivery Network).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It picks a cached version of your image from the server closest to your geographical location. This will speed up your website since it limits the number of internet hops it takes to display your image from your original server (your web hosting provider).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To learn more about CDN and how to connect your site, you can check out WPBeginner’s guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-install-wordpress-cdn-solution-maxcdn/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to install and set up WordPress CDN</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"make-your-website-mobile-friendly\">17. Make Your Website Mobile-Friendly</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Why is this important for image SEO, you may think?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Because the rise of mobile devices has made failure to look after mobile SEO a death sentence. Google won’t show your content in image search if your site isn’t optimized for mobile. In fact, Google now has a mobile-first index and ranks mobile-friendly sites higher.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to make your site mobile-friendly is to use a responsive WordPress theme that adapts to different screen sizes and devices. To find a responsive theme, please visit WPBeginner’s post on the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-responsive-wordpress-themes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">44 best responsive WordPress themes</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"prepare-for-google-lens-visual-search\">18. Prepare for Google Lens Visual Search</h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img width=\"512\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-lens.png\" alt=\"Prepare for Google Lens visual search\" class=\"wp-image-31237\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-lens.png 512w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-lens-300x146.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re running, for example, an eCommerce store or a restaurant, you need to prepare for visual search by <a href=\"https://lens.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google Lens</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Lens is Google’s new image-recognition tool. It lets users tap and hold an image in the Google app or Chrome browser on Android to find where they can buy a product or order a meal.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This feature will soon be added to the Google app on iOS as well.&nbsp;So it can be a good idea to optimize your images for Google Lens.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, did this make you feel overwhelmed?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s actually easier than it seems…</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;if you use all these tips to optimize your images in WordPress, you’ll be long on your way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you understand why image SEO is important and how you can leverage image SEO to improve rankings on Google Images and drive more traffic to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide</a> or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\">blog post SEO checklist</a> to learn how to boost rankings even more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-630d2c5969107 wp-block-buttons\"></div>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-best-optimize-images-in-wordpress/\">Image SEO: How To Best Optimize Your Images In WordPress (18 Tips)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-best-optimize-images-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"8 Best WordPress RSS Feed Plugins [2022 Edition]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:126:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-rss-feed-plugins/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=best-wordpress-rss-feed-plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-rss-feed-plugins/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 25 Aug 2022 13:22:25 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"best WordPress rss feed plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"rss feed plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"rss feeds\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=106374\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:430:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress RSS feed plugins? Really Simple Syndication or Rich Site Summary (RSS) is a type of web feed that enables users and applications to receive real-time updates from a website. In simple words, RSS&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-rss-feed-plugins/\">8 Best WordPress RSS Feed Plugins [2022 Edition]</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20760:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress RSS feed plugins?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Really Simple Syndication or Rich Site Summary (RSS) is a type of web feed that enables users and applications to receive real-time updates from a website. In simple words, RSS lets you offer your users the ability to automatically receive new content from you via an RSS feed reader, email newsletter, and other apps.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you our expertly curated list of the best WordPress RSS feed plugins you should consider.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why Use an RSS Feed Plugin?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-customize-the-rss-feed-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Customize the RSS Feed in WordPress (3 Simple Steps)\">RSS feeds</a> are an excellent way to drive traffic to your content and boost engagement.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, WordPress has built-in RSS functionality and publishes RSS feeds for your blog posts, categories, authors, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, why would you need to install an RSS feed plugin?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While WordPress has an RSS widget by default, it doesn&#8217;t let you customize your RSS feeds. For example, you can&#8217;t add thumbnails, social buttons, and other elements that drive engagement. That&#8217;s why many savvy marketers use an RSS plugin for the added functionality.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Best WordPress RSS Feed Plugins: Our Expert Picks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you find yourself being limited by WordPress&#8217;s default RSS feed, you&#8217;re probably looking for a better alternative. We&#8217;ve curated a list of some of the best RSS feeds on the market to help bolster your content marketing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>  </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best WordPress RSS plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO </a>is a powerful WordPress SEO plugin trusted by over 3 million savvy website owners to help boost their rankings and drive more traffic to their sites. The plugin has many features and modules designed to help you optimize your website for SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the powerful features of AIOSEO is its <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/rss-content/\" title=\"RSS Content\">RSS management</a> functionality.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using AIOSEO, you can easily add content to the beginning or end (footer) of your RSS feed. To do this, simply go to your AIOSEO dashboard in WordPress then select <strong>General Settings » RSS Content</strong>. Here, you can add and customize your RSS content. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"464\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-aioseo-rss.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO makes it easy to add an RSS feed to the footer of your content.\" class=\"wp-image-113850\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-aioseo-rss.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-aioseo-rss-300x199.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-aioseo-rss-600x398.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding content to your RSS footer is a great way to prevent content scraping, as it will ensure you get a link back to your content. This way, users and search engines will know that you&#8217;re the original creator of the content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another powerful feature users love about AIOSEO&#8217;s RSS feature is that it allows you <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/disable-rss-feeds-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Disable RSS Feeds in WordPress (Step by Step)\">to disable unnecessary RSS feeds easily</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"402\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-aioseo-1.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO allows you to easily disable your RSS feeds in WordPress.\" class=\"wp-image-113689\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-aioseo-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-aioseo-1-300x172.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-aioseo-1-600x345.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is something you can&#8217;t do with WordPress&#8217;s default RSS settings. Disabling feeds you don&#8217;t use is an excellent way of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-delete-url-parameters-from-google-search-console/\" title=\"How to Delete URL Parameters from Google Search Console (The Easy Way)\">getting rid of URL parameters</a> that serve no purpose but to eat up your crawl budget.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part about AIOSEO is that anyone can use the powerful plugin, even if you have no coding or technical knowledge.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed instructions on how to install AIOSEO, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: AIOSEO has a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/all-in-one-seo-pack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">free version</a> with basic WordPress SEO features. To unlock all the features, you’ll need the Pro version, which starts at $49.50.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rss-aggregator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">WP RSS Aggregator</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rss-aggregator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"371\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-wp-rss-aggregator.png\" alt=\"WP RSS Aggregator is one of the best WordPress RSS feed plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-110736\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-wp-rss-aggregator.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-wp-rss-aggregator-300x159.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-wp-rss-aggregator-600x318.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rss-aggregator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">WP RSS Aggregator</a> is undoubtedly one of the best WordPress RSS plugins on the market, as seen by the over 2 million downloads it boasts. The plugin allows you to easily import, merge, and display RSS feeds on your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another useful feature you&#8217;ll find with WP RSS Aggregator is that it allows you to fetch content from your other web properties. You can also use it to aggregate any content, including audio and visuals from third-party sources and store it in your WordPress database.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $59/year for a single site license.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. <a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/custom-facebook-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Smash Balloon Custom Facebook Feed</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/custom-facebook-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"324\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-facebook.png\" alt=\"Smash Balloon Facebook Feed Pro is the best WordPress RSS feed plugin for Facebook feeds.\" class=\"wp-image-110762\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-facebook.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-facebook-300x139.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-facebook-600x278.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If your social media marketing relies heavily on Facebook, then <a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/custom-facebook-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Smash Balloon Custom Facebook Feed</a> is the best Facebook feed plugin for you. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin allows you to display the latest posts from your Facebook groups and pages right on your WordPress site. This is an excellent way of boosting engagement with your Facebook posts as you are not at the mercy of Facebook&#8217;s algorithm.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Smash Balloon Custom Facebook Feed is easy to use and allows you to connect as many groups and pages as you like. It also offers the flexibility of using multiple feeds in different areas of your website. The customization options are endless.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Smash Balloon has a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-facebook-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">free Facebook feed plugin</a> with limited features. Paid plans start at $49/year for a single site license. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. <a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/instagram-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Smash Balloon Instagram Feed</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/instagram-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"325\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-instagram.png\" alt=\"Smash Balloon Instagram Feed Pro is the best WordPress RSS feed plugin for Instagram feeds.\" class=\"wp-image-110774\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-instagram.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-instagram-300x139.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-instagram-600x279.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/instagram-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Smash Balloon Instagram Feeds</a> is another WordPress RSS plugin to consider if you publish visual content. If you&#8217;re an Instagram user, you&#8217;ve probably noticed that the platform doesn’t make it easy to use RSS feeds. Smash Balloon uses Instagram&#8217;s API to automatically display photos from your Instagram account right onto your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the reasons users love the plugin is its ease of use. Plus, it comes with multiple layout styles, making customization a breeze. And if you run an e-commerce store, you can directly link your Instagram posts to your product pages in WooCommerce. This is a powerful way to increase sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free version available. Custom Instagram Feed Pro starts from $49/year for a single site license. Alternatively, you can get all Smash Balloon plugins for unlimited sites at $299 per year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/themeisle-feedzy-rss-feeds/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Feedzy RSS Feeds</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/themeisle-feedzy-rss-feeds/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"330\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-feedzy.png\" alt=\"Feedzy is another WordPress RSS plugin to have on your radar.\" class=\"wp-image-113376\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-feedzy.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-feedzy-300x141.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-feedzy-600x283.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/themeisle-feedzy-rss-feeds/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Feedzy RSS Feeds</a> is another WordPress RSS feed plugin you should have on your radar. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin allows you to fetch content from unlimited RSS feeds and display them on your website. It also comes with several templates to help you customize how you display feeds. You can also rearrange the feed layout, making your feed content look native to your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For affiliate marketers, Feedzy has a feature that allows you to integrate your affiliate links into feeds, allowing you to display products with your affiliate ID. As a result, you can increase your chances of earning affiliate commissions by aggregating content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $59 per year.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. <a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/youtube-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Smash Balloon Feeds for YouTube</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/youtube-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"316\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-youtube.png\" alt=\"Smash Balloon YouTube Feed Pro is the best WordPress RSS feed plugin for YouTube feeds.\" class=\"wp-image-113378\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-youtube.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-youtube-300x136.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-smash-balloon-youtube-600x271.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/youtube-feed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Smash Balloon Feeds for YouTube</a> is a fantastic YouTube feed plugin for WordPress. It allows you to easily showcase your YouTube videos on your website, thereby helping you generate more views for your videos.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sure, by default, WordPress allows you to display Youtube videos on your site. But to do so, you need to copy and paste the video URL manually on your site. Smash Balloon Feeds for YouTube helps you automate this process. The feed plugin also gives you more flexibility over design options and how the videos get displayed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For greater customization, you can create custom feeds using keywords, multiple channels, and even combine feeds. You can also add custom actions to your feeds. For example, when a YouTube video ends, you can display a link to a product page or display thumbnails of other videos on your channel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free plan available. The Pro plan starts at $49 per year for a single site license.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/super-rss-reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Super RSS Reader</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/super-rss-reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"323\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-super-rss-reader.png\" alt=\"Super RSS Reader is one of the best WordPress RSS feed plugins in the WordPress repository.\" class=\"wp-image-113387\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-super-rss-reader.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-super-rss-reader-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-super-rss-reader-600x277.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for the best free WordPress RSS feed plugin, then <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/super-rss-reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Super RSS Reader</a> could be it. The plugin gives users an excellent way to display content from multiple RSS feeds in the WordPress sidebar.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One thing you&#8217;ll love about the plugin is that it comes with an easy-to-use widget. The widget makes it easy to use the plugin to display RSS feeds in an attractive way. For example, if you run a news site, you can display post titles as a news ticker. You can also display feeds from multiple sources in a tab layout. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Despite being a simple plugin, Super RSS Reader offers many customization options.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>8. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/featured-images-for-rss-feeds/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Featured Image in RSS Feed</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/featured-images-for-rss-feeds/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"319\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-featured-images-rss.png\" alt=\"Featured Images in RSS is one of the best WordPress RSS feed plugins in the WordPress repository.\" class=\"wp-image-113392\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-featured-images-rss.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-featured-images-rss-300x137.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/best-wordpress-rss-plugins-featured-images-rss-600x273.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/featured-images-for-rss-feeds/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Featured Image in RSS</a> is a WordPress plugin that makes it super easy to add featured images to your RSS feeds without writing code. The plugin gives various styling options for your thumbnails or featured images.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin uses standard formatting options for the featured image. This allows news aggregators like Feedly to easily detect and display it. Featured Image in RSS Feed also works with most of the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-email-marketing-services/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">top email marketing services</a> that support the RSS to email list feature.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free version available. Paid plans start at $59.88 per year for a single site license.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Best WordPress RSS Feed Plugins: Our Expert Pick</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re looking for the best WordPress RSS plugin, then <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is definitely your best option. The plugin is super easy to use and has a robust feature set. The best part is, with AIOSEO installed, you don’t have to add a dedicated RSS plugin to your site. This will help you keep your plugin count to a minimum, resulting in better site performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if your business relies a lot on social media marketing, then <a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Smash Balloon</a> should be your go-to RSS feed plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you’re on a shoestring budget and are looking for the best free WordPress RSS plugin, then we highly recommend <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/super-rss-reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Super RSS Reader</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you pick the right WordPress RSS plugin for your site. Once you’re done setting up your RSS feeds, you may also want to see our tutorial on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-avoid-404-errors-when-updating-your-wordpress-site/\" title=\"How to Avoid 404 Errors When Updating Your WordPress Site\">how to avoid 404 errors</a> on your WordPress site and our expert pick of the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-table-of-contents-plugins-for-wordpress/\" title=\"8 Best Table of Contents Plugins for WordPress for 2022\">best table of contents plugins</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-rss-feed-plugins/\">8 Best WordPress RSS Feed Plugins [2022 Edition]</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-rss-feed-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"8 Proven Ways to Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:160:\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 22 Aug 2022 12:23:10 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"conversion rate optimization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"increase organic clickthrough rates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"increase organic CTR\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"organic clickthrough rates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"organic CTR\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=109542\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:463:\"<p>Would you like to increase your organic clickthrough rates (CTR)? The higher the CTR on your blog posts and landing pages, the more traffic you drive to your site, leading to increased revenue for your business. In this article, we&#8217;ll&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/\">8 Proven Ways to Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24333:\"<p>Would you like to increase your organic clickthrough rates (CTR)?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The higher the CTR on your blog posts and landing pages, the more traffic you drive to your site, leading to increased revenue for your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll share some of the top tips we use to increase our organic CTR.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-organic-clickthrough-rate\">What is Organic Clickthrough Rate?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-why-is-increasing-your-organic-ctr-important\">Why is Increasing Your Organic Clickthrough Rates Important?</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-8-ways-to-increase-organic-clickthrough-rates\">8 Ways to Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-1-aim-for-the-top-spot-on-serps\">1. Aim for the Top Spot on SERPs</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-2-optimize-serp-snippets-for-visibility\">2. Optimize SERP Snippets for Visibility</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-3-use-jump-links-to-boost-your-ctr\">3. Use Jump Links to Boost Your CTR</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-4-use-the-right-keywords-in-the-right-places\">4. Use the Right Keywords in the Right Places</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-5-nail-your-search-intent\">5. Nail Your Search Intent</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-6-write-irresistible-seo-titles\">6. Write Irresistible SEO Titles</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-7-craft-optimized-meta-descriptions\">7. Craft Optimized Meta Descriptions</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-8-use-seo-friendly-url-structures\">8. Use SEO-friendly URL Structures</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates-and-grow-your-business\">Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates and Grow Your Business</a></li></ul></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-is-organic-clickthrough-rate\">What is Organic Clickthrough Rate?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Organic clickthrough rate (CTR) is the percentage of users who click on your search listing on search engine results pages (SERPs). For example, if 50 people see your listing and 5 people click on it, then your CTR would be 10%. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-why-is-increasing-your-organic-ctr-important\">Why is Increasing Your Organic Clickthrough Rates Important?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Increasing your organic CTR has many SEO and business benefits. Here are the top 3:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>More organic traffic</strong>: An increase in organic CTR means more people are clicking on your search listing, resulting in more organic traffic to your site. This means a better ROI for your SEO campaigns.</li><li><strong>Better SEO rankings</strong>: High CTRs signal to search engines that your content is valuable to users. As a result, they rank your content better.</li><li><strong>Increased revenue</strong>: An increase in organic CTR can ultimately lead to increased revenue for your business. This is because of the increase in traffic and leads.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>While many businesses focus on boosting their SEO rankings, this alone is only part of the equation for having an impactful online presence. After all, ranking high is useless if people don&#8217;t click on your search listings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-8-ways-to-increase-organic-clickthrough-rates\">8 Ways to Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>So, how do you improve your organic clickthrough rate?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some proven ways to help you do so.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-1-aim-for-the-top-spot-on-serps\">1. Aim for the Top Spot on SERPs</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first steps to increasing your organic clickthrough rate is to rank high on SERPs. Research shows that about <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/digital-marketing-statistics/#seostatistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">67% of clicks on SERPs</a> go to the first 5 results, meaning the higher you rank, the better your CTR.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, how can you improve your chances of ranking high in search?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the best ways is to use a powerful SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"All In One SEO\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO). </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best SEO plugins on the market and can help you increase your organic CTR.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is one of the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress/\" title=\"8 Best SEO Plugins for WordPress in 2022 (Tried and Tested)\">best WordPress SEO plugins</a> on the market. The over 100 million downloads are a perfect testament to that. That’s why smart website owners use AIOSEO to help them boost their search rankings and drive qualified traffic to their sites. One reason is the plugin&#8217;s powerful features can help you properly configure your SEO settings. Examples include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Sitemap generator for improved crawling by search engines</li><li>TrueSEO analysis for on-page optimization</li><li>Advanced schema settings for rich snippets on SERPs</li><li>Link Assistant for optimized internal links on autopilot</li><li>A Redirection Manager to eliminate 404 errors</li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\" title=\"Features\">And more</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the SEO modules in AIOSEO, ranking your website and content becomes much easier. As a result, you&#8217;ll enjoy a boost in organic clickthrough rates.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part is you don&#8217;t need any coding or technical knowledge to use AIOSEO&#8217;s powerful features, making it easier for you to rise to the top of the SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-2-optimize-serp-snippets-for-visibility\">2. Optimize SERP Snippets for Visibility</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to increase your organic clickthrough rate is to optimize your SERP snippets for visibility. This means making your search snippets more prominent on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The more prominent your listing is on SERPs, the more likely users will click on it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to optimize your snippets for visibility is by using an FAQ block that outputs JSON schema. This is another reason AIOSEO should be your SEO toolkit of choice. The plugin has a powerful FAQ block that automatically outputs schema markup, resulting in bigger and more visible listings on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"385\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-faq.png\" alt=\"Adding an FAQ section is an excellent way to increase your organic clickthrough rates.\" class=\"wp-image-109636\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-faq.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-faq-300x165.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-faq-600x330.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Notice how Investopedia&#8217;s listing is more prominent than the others because of the FAQs. Because it stands out, users are more likely to click on it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can leverage the same strategy to get bigger and more prominent listings in search. Go ahead and check out this article for step-by-step instructions on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\" title=\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\">how to easily add an FAQ section in WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way to optimize your snippets for visibility on SERPs is by using schema markup for rich snippets.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"423\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-rich-snippets.png\" alt=\"Rich snippets are another powerful way to increase organic clickthrough rates.\" class=\"wp-image-109646\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-rich-snippets.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-rich-snippets-300x181.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-rich-snippets-600x363.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the above example, the third listing is likely to drive more clicks than the 2 listings above it because of the rich snippets. The extra information like the star rating, cooking time, and votes inspire confidence in users, thereby resulting in a higher CTR.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An easy way to add schema markup to your content and get rich snippets is to use AIOSEO&#8217;s schema markup feature to get rich snippets like these.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To add schema markup, simply scroll down the page you&#8217;re editing until you get to AIOSEO&#8217;s settings. Next, click on the <strong>Schema</strong> tab, then select your schema type. The plugin will automatically output the appropriate schema type for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"414\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-rich-snippets-aioseo.png\" alt=\"You can add schema markup using AIOSEO\'s schema feature.\" class=\"wp-image-109650\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-rich-snippets-aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-rich-snippets-aioseo-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-rich-snippets-aioseo-600x355.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part is both methods mentioned above are easy to implement, even if you&#8217;re a non-technical person.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-3-use-jump-links-to-boost-your-ctr\">3. Use Jump Links to Boost Your CTR</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Jump links are another effective way of increasing your organic CTR.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are jump links on SERPs?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Jump links are hyperlinks that direct users to specific parts of a page instead of the entire page.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png\" alt=\"A table of contents results in jump links, leading to an increase in your organic clickthrough rates.\" class=\"wp-image-105094\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-300x126.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-600x252.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The hyperlinks at the bottom of the snippet in the example above are jump links that take users directly to those sections of the article. To leverage jump links in your snippets, you need to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)\">add a table of contents in your blog posts</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding an SEO-friendly table of contents is super easy with AIOSEO. The plugin has a powerful table of contents block that automatically creates a table of contents from your subheadings. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png\" alt=\"The Table of Content blocks helps you automatically create a table of contents on your posts.\" class=\"wp-image-104817\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-600x339.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s a guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)\">how to use the Table of Contents block</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Publishing content with tables of contents is a powerful way of having jump links included in your search snippets. And the jump links will increase your organic CTR.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-4-use-the-right-keywords-in-the-right-places\">4. Use the Right Keywords in the Right Places</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Keywords are the foundation of all on-page SEO strategies. After all, for your target audience to find you online, you must know which keywords they use to search for information.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fortunately, uncovering these keywords is pretty easy with <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-keyword-analysis-tool/\" title=\"8 Best SEO Keyword Analysis Tools You Need to Know in 2022\">keyword research tools</a> like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a>, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Semrush</a>, and others. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>After you find the right keywords, you must use them in the right places. To help improve your CTR, you should include keywords in your URL, SEO title, and meta description.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By placing your keywords strategically in these places, users will see right on the SERPs that your content contains the information they&#8217;re looking for. As a result, more people will click on your listing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-5-nail-your-search-intent\">5. Nail Your Search Intent</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another proven way of increasing your organic CTR is to demonstrate that your content will meet search intent. Search intent simply means the reason users are looking for that particular piece of information. These reasons can be grouped into 4 common buckets:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Informational</strong>: This is when users simply want to know more about a particular topic. </li><li><strong>Navigational</strong>: This type of intent is displayed when users look for a particular page. </li><li><strong>Commercial</strong>: Commercial search intent is displayed when a user is researching a product and intends to buy it soon.</li><li><strong>Transactional</strong>: With transactional search intent, users are actively looking for a solution and are ready to buy at that moment.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowing why users want information about a particular keyword will help you tailor your content to match that intent. To boost your organic CTR, demonstrate search intent in your SEO title, meta description, and URL. When you do so, the result will be an increase in your organic CTR.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Figuring out search intent may seem complicated, but it really isn&#8217;t. To discover the intent behind a keyword, plug it into a search engine and observe the top-ranking articles. You can also get intent data from tools like GSC and Semrush.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-6-write-irresistible-seo-titles\">6. Write Irresistible SEO Titles </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO titles are crucial in helping increase organic clickthrough rates because they&#8217;re the first snippet element a user sees on SERPs. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"316\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-post-title-1.png\" alt=\"Compelling SEO titles are a great way to boost your organic clickthrough rates.\" class=\"wp-image-110081\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-post-title-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-post-title-1-300x135.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-post-title-1-600x271.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why you must optimize your SEO titles to encourage users to click on your listing. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re an AIOSEO user, this is easy as the plugin makes it easy to optimize your titles for search. Simply open your post and scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO General </strong>settings. To set the SEO title, click on one of the smart tags above the <strong>Post Title</strong> field. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"347\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-post-title.png\" alt=\"Use tags to configure your SEO title Format or simply type it into the Post Title field.\" class=\"wp-image-110066\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-post-title.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-post-title-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-post-title-600x297.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These will set the SEO title format to output on SERPs. AIOSEO will automatically pull your SEO title from your post&#8217;s headline in the desired format. Alternatively, you can manually type in an optimized version in the <strong>Post Title</strong> field.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Two powerful ways to optimize your SEO titles include adding your focus keyword and matching your title to search intent. You should also keep your SEO title as short as possible to avoid it being truncated on SERPs. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-7-craft-optimized-meta-descriptions\">7. Craft Optimized Meta Descriptions</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Meta descriptions are another important element that can help you increase your organic CTR. They are HTML snippets used to describe the content on a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/posts-vs-pages-in-wordpress/\" title=\"Posts vs. Pages in WordPress — Everything You Need to Know\">post or page</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"385\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-meta-description-1.png\" alt=\"Craft an optimized meta description to help you jncrease your organic clickthrough rates.  \" class=\"wp-image-110083\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-meta-description-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-meta-description-1-300x165.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-meta-description-1-600x330.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An optimized meta description does more than describe the content on that page. It&#8217;s also a sales pitch to convince users to click on your listing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Again, this is where an SEO plugin like AIOSEO helps, as it makes it easy to optimize your meta descriptions. To do so, you can scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO General</strong> settings tab, where you&#8217;ll find the <strong>Meta Description</strong> field. Type your meta description as you want it to appear in your SERP snippet. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-meta-description.png\" alt=\"Use the Meta Description field to type in and optimize your meta description.\" class=\"wp-image-110069\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-meta-description.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-meta-description-300x193.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-meta-description-600x386.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An optimized meta description must:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Promise an answer to users&#8217; questions</li><li>Include your focus keyword</li><li>Paint a picture of the benefits of clicking on your content</li><li>Use active voice to encourage users to take action</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Crafted well, your meta description help encourage users to click on your search listing, thereby increasing your organic CTR.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-8-use-seo-friendly-url-structures\">8. Use SEO-friendly URL Structures</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>URLs are underutilized when it comes to SEO and conversion rate optimization. Yet they are a powerful element of your snippet that can be used to boost your CTR. Because they are visible in your snippet, they impact how users will respond to your listing on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One way to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-permalink-structure/\" title=\"What’s the Best WordPress Permalink Structure for SEO?\">make your URLs SEO-friendly</a> includes making them short and descriptive, as in the example below.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"502\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-urls-1.png\" alt=\"Short and descriptive URLs are an important element of increasing your organic clickthrough rates.\" class=\"wp-image-109904\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-urls-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-urls-1-300x215.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-urls-1-600x430.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another tip is to include your focus keyword. This will help reinforce what your post is about. Also, eliminate dates and numbers to help keep your URLs evergreen. This helps ensure users find your URL appealing even if your post is older than newer alternatives on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To edit and optimize your URL slug, head over to your <strong>Post</strong> options in the WordPress editor&#8217;s sidebar. Next, scroll down to your <strong>Permalink</strong> settings and edit your URL slug.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"385\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-url-3.png\" alt=\"Edit your URL slug in the Permalink section of the WordPress editor\'s sidebar.\" class=\"wp-image-110072\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-url-3.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-url-3-300x165.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/increase-organic-ctr-url-3-600x330.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your URLs is also good for SEO as it helps search engines understand what your page is about, leading to better indexing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates-and-grow-your-business\">Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates and Grow Your Business</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Having a strong online presence is crucial to business growth. But that growth can only come if people find your content and click on it on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business growth is a result of good clickthrough rates. And we believe that if you use the tips above, then you&#8217;ll get more people clicking on your search listing, resulting in more traffic and leads.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you know how to increase your organic clickthrough rates (CTR). Once you&#8217;re done optimizing your content for better CTRs, you may also want to check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-tutorial/\" title=\"A Simple SEO Tutorial for Beginners: The Ultimate Guide\">SEO tutorial for beginners </a>or our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\" title=\"A Complete Blog Post SEO Checklist to Boost Rankings\">complete blog post SEO checklist</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/\">8 Proven Ways to Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"How to Avoid 404 Errors When Updating Your WordPress Site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:178:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-avoid-404-errors-when-updating-your-wordpress-site/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-avoid-404-errors-when-updating-your-wordpress-site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-avoid-404-errors-when-updating-your-wordpress-site/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 18 Aug 2022 13:32:30 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Avoiding 404 errors\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"page not found error\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"wordpress 404 errors\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=109009\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:443:\"<p>Would you like to know how to avoid 404 errors that may come up whenever you update your WordPress site? Updating your site may require you to edit your URL slugs, and if not handled properly, this could lead to&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-avoid-404-errors-when-updating-your-wordpress-site/\">How to Avoid 404 Errors When Updating Your WordPress Site</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9115:\"<p>Would you like to know how to avoid 404 errors that may come up whenever you update your WordPress site?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Updating your site may require you to edit your URL slugs, and if not handled properly, this could lead to 404 errors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to avoid 404 errors when you update your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What are 404 Errors (And Why Should You Avoid Them)?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>404 errors in WordPress mean that the URL to a web page you’re trying to visit is broken, or the page doesn’t exist anymore. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"327\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/how-to-avoid-404-errors-in-wordpress-we-are-social.png\" alt=\"Here\'s an example of a 404 error.\" class=\"wp-image-109589\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/how-to-avoid-404-errors-in-wordpress-we-are-social.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/how-to-avoid-404-errors-in-wordpress-we-are-social-300x140.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/how-to-avoid-404-errors-in-wordpress-we-are-social-600x280.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This usually happens when a page has been deleted. It also happens when a URL slug has been edited, but no <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-301-redirects-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add 301 Redirects in WordPress (Beginner’s Guide)\">proper redirection</a> has been implemented. As a result, while browsers may be able to connect to your site, they won&#8217;t be able to find that particular page. This is why a 404 error is sometimes called a &#8220;page not found&#8221; error.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Are 404 Errors Harmful to Your SEO?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, 404 errors are harmful to your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the biggest dangers of 404 errors is that they result in poor user experience (UX). UX is an important ranking element that makes up Google&#8217;s Page Experience ranking signals.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another reason 404 errors are bad for SEO is that they lead to high bounce rates. If users don&#8217;t find the page they are looking for, they&#8217;ll quickly go elsewhere. The high bounce rate on that page will signal to search engines that your page has poor quality content, resulting in the page being de-ranked.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides the UX factor, pages with 404 errors are still crawled by search engines, resulting in a wasted crawl budget. 404 errors also indicate poor site health, an element that weakens your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-technical-seo-the-best-checklist-in-2022/\" title=\"What Is Technical SEO? The Best Checklist in 2022\">technical SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-easily-find-and-fix-404-errors-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Easily Find and Fix 404 Errors in WordPress\">properly dealing with 404 errors</a> on your WordPress site can ultimately lead to you losing all your SEO gains for that page.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>These and more reasons are why you must avoid 404 errors at all costs. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Avoid 404 Errors When Updating Your WordPress Site</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>So, how can you avoid 404 errors when updating your WordPress site?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to avoiding 404 errors when updating your WordPress site is to install <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" title=\"All In One SEO (AIOSEO)\">All In One SEO (AIOSEO)</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best SEO plugins on the market and has powerful features to help you avoid 404 errors in WordPress.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is a powerful WordPress SEO plugin and toolkit. It&#8217;s used on over 3 million websites to improve SEO rankings and increase site traffic. The plugin boasts many powerful features, including advanced SEO modules, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\" title=\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\">an FAQ block</a>, a sitemap generator, and many more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To help you avoid 404 errors when updating your WordPress site, the plugin also comes with a powerful URL Slug Monitor. This feature automatically detects changes in a URL and guides you into implementing a redirect. And you don&#8217;t even need any technical or coding knowledge to use this feature to avoid 404 errors. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please see <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">our step-by-step guide</a> for detailed instructions on installing and activating AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you update your content, AIOSEO&#8217;s URL Slug Monitor automatically checks for any changes in your URLs. If the slug monitor detects a URL change, it will prompt you to add a redirect.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"338\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/url-slug-monitor-new.png\" alt=\"The URL Slug Monitor is a powerful tool for anyone who wants to know how to avoid 404 errors when editing permalinks.\" class=\"wp-image-105047\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/url-slug-monitor-new.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/url-slug-monitor-new-300x145.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/url-slug-monitor-new-600x290.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you get the prompt, click the <strong>Add Redirect to improve SEO</strong> button. This will open a window where you can implement your redirects.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/how-to-avoid-404-errors-in-wordpress-2.png\" alt=\"Type in your source and destination URLs and click on Add Redirect. \" class=\"wp-image-109348\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/how-to-avoid-404-errors-in-wordpress-2.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/how-to-avoid-404-errors-in-wordpress-2-300x131.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/how-to-avoid-404-errors-in-wordpress-2-600x262.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Type in your source and destination URLs and click on <strong>Add Redirect</strong>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One powerful feature you&#8217;ll love about AIOSEO is that the plugin also lets you track all 404 errors on your site. You can do this by heading to the <strong>404 Logs</strong> section. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-logs-1.png\" alt=\"The 404 Logs section keeps track of all pages that return a 404 error, allowing you to easily fix them.\" class=\"wp-image-111016\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-logs-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-logs-1-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-logs-1-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If there are any pages with 404 errors in the log, you can easily fix and redirect them with a few clicks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that&#8217;s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ve avoided having a 404 error while updating your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you avoid 404 errors when updating your WordPress site. Once you’re done updating your content, you may also want to check out our articles on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\" title=\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\">how to add an FAQ section</a> to your blog posts and our tutorial on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-social-media-profiles-to-your-wordpress-sites-schema/\" title=\"How to Add Social Media Profiles to Your WordPress Site’s Schema\">how to add social media profiles</a> to your WordPress site helpful.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-avoid-404-errors-when-updating-your-wordpress-site/\">How to Avoid 404 Errors When Updating Your WordPress Site</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-avoid-404-errors-when-updating-your-wordpress-site/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"Announcing AIOSEO 4.2.4: Improved Redirects and Image SEO Updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:192:\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-aioseo-4-2-4-improved-redirects-and-image-seo-updates/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=announcing-aioseo-4-2-4-improved-redirects-and-image-seo-updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-aioseo-4-2-4-improved-redirects-and-image-seo-updates/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 16 Aug 2022 11:54:48 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Image SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"redirection manager\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=111009\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:497:\"<p>Your favorite WordPress SEO plugin just got better. Today, I&#8217;m excited to share our newest release AIOSEO 4.2.4 which comes packed with powerful features that you&#8217;ve been asking for. The overall goal of this release is to help you improve&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-aioseo-4-2-4-improved-redirects-and-image-seo-updates/\">Announcing AIOSEO 4.2.4: Improved Redirects and Image SEO Updates</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Benjamin Rojas\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8491:\"<p>Your favorite WordPress SEO plugin just got better.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, I&#8217;m excited to share our newest release AIOSEO 4.2.4 which comes packed with powerful features that you&#8217;ve been asking for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The overall goal of this release is to help you improve your SEO rankings with new image SEO module features as well as our much improved Redirection Manager.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s quickly look at how you can utilize these new features.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Eliminate 404 Errors With Our Massively Improved Redirection Manager</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In AIOSEO 4.2.4, we made several major improvements to our Redirection Manager module based on your feedback, so you can easily manage your redirects and avoid 404 errors.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We added a new feature that automatically lets you redirect all 404 pages to either your Homepage or the parent page or category. Aside from that, we still track visits to these in the 404 log, so you can always manually redirect the URL to another custom page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To use this feature, you can enable it from the Redirects settings section.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"405\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-settings.png\" alt=\"The Redirection manager will help you easily redirect these URLs to their parent, category, or home pages.\" class=\"wp-image-111012\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-settings.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-settings-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-settings-600x347.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you run an e-commerce store, the updated 404 settings features will redirect products and product categories without a direct parent to the <strong>Shop</strong> page if one is set.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"261\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-to-shop.png\" alt=\"If you run an e-commerce store, the updated 404 settings features will redirect products and product categories without a direct parent to the Shop page.\" class=\"wp-image-111013\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-to-shop.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-to-shop-300x112.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-to-shop-600x224.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will help prevent customers from bouncing off your site and keep them on your store longer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Based on popular request, we added a search feature in our Redirection Manager, so you can easily search through 404 logs and easily add redirects with just a click.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-logs-01.png\" alt=\"The Redirection Manager now also comes with a search function that allows you to search your redirect and 404 logs.\" class=\"wp-image-111017\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-logs-01.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-logs-01-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-404-logs-01-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another UX improvement that we added based on user feedback is removing the number of clicks it take to setup a redirect when you delete a post or page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, you’ll notice that all our redirect prompts open in a modal that allows you to add the redirect without taking you to the Redirection Manager. This eliminates a couple of steps in the process, making it easier and faster to implement redirects.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"354\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-modal-window.png\" alt=\"Our redirect prompts now open a modal that allows you to add the redirect without taking you to the Redirection Manager.\" class=\"wp-image-111018\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-modal-window.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-modal-window-300x152.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/redirects-modal-window-600x303.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With the improvements we’ve made to our redirection manager, managing your redirects is much easier. As a result, you’ll have fewer instances of 404 errors. This will lead to a better user experience (UX), a major ranking factor since Google announced their Page Experience ranking signals.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Rank Better With More Powerful Image SEO Settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Images play a huge role in making your content more engaging, educational, and interactive. Used well, images are a great tool to help you boost your SEO. Hence image SEO must be part of your overall SEO strategy.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s why we’ve made major improvements to our Image SEO module.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new features will allow you to optimize your image titles, alt tags, captions, descriptions, and file names easily. It does this by enabling you to choose characters to strip automatically.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"468\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-seo-strip-characters.png\" alt=\"The new Image SEO features will allow you to optimize your image titles, alt tags, captions, descriptions, and file names easily.\" class=\"wp-image-111019\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-seo-strip-characters.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-seo-strip-characters-300x201.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-seo-strip-characters-600x401.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Image SEO functionality also lets you choose the characters you want to convert to spaces or sentence casing. You can also choose the pages and posts to implement these settings on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"491\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-seo-strip-characters-1.png\" alt=\"The new Image SEO functionality also lets you choose the characters you want to convert to spaces or sentence casing. \" class=\"wp-image-111020\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-seo-strip-characters-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-seo-strip-characters-1-300x210.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-seo-strip-characters-1-600x421.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We designed all these image SEO settings to help make it easier for your images to rank for relevant search terms. As a result, your content will also become more discoverable.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides these 2 major updates, we’ve made several notable improvements to many of the features you already love. You can see those in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/changelog/\" title=\"AIOSEO product changelog\">full product changelog</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are you waiting for? Update your site to AIOSEO 4.2.4 to unlock these new powerful features.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you’re not yet using AIOSEO, make sure to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">install and activate the plugin today</a>. This one SEO plugin you can trust to help you outrank your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have any questions about these features, please comment below or reach out to our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/contact/\" title=\"Contact Us\">customer support team</a>. We&#8217;re always ready to help.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our commitment to making AIOSEO the easiest and best WordPress SEO plugin is only getting stronger as we continue to win together with our customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;re so grateful for your continued support, feedback, and suggestions. Please keep those suggestions and feature requests coming.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope you enjoy using these new SEO features as much as we enjoyed creating it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>– Benjamin Rojas</em></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-aioseo-4-2-4-improved-redirects-and-image-seo-updates/\">Announcing AIOSEO 4.2.4: Improved Redirects and Image SEO Updates</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-aioseo-4-2-4-improved-redirects-and-image-seo-updates/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"8 Best Table of Contents Plugins for WordPress for 2022\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:152:\"https://aioseo.com/best-table-of-contents-plugins-for-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=best-table-of-contents-plugins-for-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://aioseo.com/best-table-of-contents-plugins-for-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 08 Aug 2022 13:09:02 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"adding table of contents in wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"best table of contents plugins for wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"wordpress table of contents plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=107983\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:444:\"<p>Are you looking for the best table of contents plugins for WordPress? A table of contents (ToC) can help improve user experience on your site, leading to increased dwell time and a boost in SEO. Unfortunately, adding one can be&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-table-of-contents-plugins-for-wordpress/\">8 Best Table of Contents Plugins for WordPress for 2022</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20717:\"<p>Are you looking for the best table of contents plugins for WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A table of contents (ToC) can help improve user experience on your site, leading to increased dwell time and a boost in SEO. Unfortunately, adding one can be laborious, especially for long-form blog posts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, will share the best tables of contents plugins for WordPress. These plugins will make <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)\">adding a table of contents to your blog posts</a> super easy. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why You Need a Table of Contents </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A table of contents has many benefits for both you and your site visitors. For one, it can help users easily navigate through your content. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But it also results in jump links that lead to higher clickthrough rates (CTR). This boosts your SEO as high CTRs signal to search engines that users love your content and find it helpful.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png\" alt=\"Adding a table of contents enhances your appearance on SERPs by inc\" class=\"wp-image-105094\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-300x126.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-600x252.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to check out our expert pick of the best WordPress table of contents plugins?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s dive right in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Best Table of Contents Plugins for WordPress: Our Top Picks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing the right table of contents plugin for your WordPress site can be difficult, given the many available options. We&#8217;ve taken the hard work out of this and curated a list of our expert picks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, let&#8217;s jump right in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best table of contents plugins for WordPress.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) is a powerful SEO plugin that boasts over 100 million downloads. Savvy marketers trust the plugin to help them rank and drive targeted traffic to their sites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you want to add a table of contents to your blog posts, you&#8217;ll find the AIOSEO-Table of Contents block super easy to use. This makes it one of the best WordPress table of contents plugins around.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin is easy to use as it identifies headings on a page and automatically adds them to your table of contents. AIOSEO also allows you to customize your table of contents, making it suit your needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png\" alt=\"The Table of Content blocks helps you automatically create a table of contents on your posts.\" class=\"wp-image-104817\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-600x339.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>You can hide elements of the table of contents</li><li>Easy to use</li><li>Change table of contents items without affecting your content</li><li>Powerful customization options</li><li>SEO-friendly</li><li>Translation ready</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The biggest advantage of using AIOSEO&#8217;s table of contents block is that once you&#8217;ve <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">installed and activated AIOSEO</a>, you won&#8217;t need to bloat your site with another table of contents plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $49 for an annual plan of the SEO plugin. A free version is also available.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/easy-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Easy Table of Contents\">Easy Table of Contents</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/easy-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"233\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-easy-table-of-contents.png\" alt=\"Easy Table of Contents is another excellent plugin to consider as you look for the best table of contents plugins for WordPress.\" class=\"wp-image-108049\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-easy-table-of-contents.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-easy-table-of-contents-300x100.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-easy-table-of-contents-600x200.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/easy-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Easy Table of Contents\">Easy Table of Contents</a> is another excellent plugin to consider as you look for the best WordPress table of comments plugin. The plugin boasts over 300,000 active installs, showing its popularity in the WordPress community. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As the name suggests, the plugin is super easy to use. You can use it to easily add a table of contents to any page or post on your site in just a few clicks. While it automatically creates tables of contents, the plugin also allows you to add them manually if you are up for it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Supports smooth scrolling</li><li>Works with most popular page builders</li><li>Multiple  bullet formats</li><li>Automatic table of contents insertion according to post type</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for a WordPress table of contents plugin suitable for beginners and experts, then Easy Table of Contents should be high on your list.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/rich-table-of-content/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Rich Table of Contents\">Rich Table of Contents</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/rich-table-of-content/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-rich.png\" alt=\"Rich Table of Contents (RTOC) is another amazing ToC plugin you must have on your radar. \" class=\"wp-image-108396\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-rich.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-rich-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-rich-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/rich-table-of-content/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Rich Table of Contents\">Rich Table of Contents</a> (RTOC) is another amazing table of contents plugin you must have on your radar. One reason for this is its simplicity. Designed with non-technical users in mind, it allows you to create a beautiful table of contents with a single click.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve created your ToC, you can customize it easily. For example, you can configure basic settings like the title, font, and the number of headings to display. You can also choose which pages and posts you want to automatically insert your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Clean and intuitive user interface</li><li>Animated table of contents</li><li>Smooth scroll</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>RTOC is a no-frills table of contents plugin for those who prefer a minimalistic look on their sites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Price</strong>: Free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/heroic-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Heroic Table of Contents\">Heroic Table of Contents Plugin</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/heroic-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-heroic.png\" alt=\"Heroic Table of Contents is another fantastic table of contents plugin for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-108521\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-heroic.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-heroic-300x135.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-heroic-600x270.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/heroic-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Heroic Table of Contents\">Heroic Table of Contents</a> is another fantastic table of contents plugin for WordPress. The plugin easily detects your subheadings and automatically adds them to your ToC.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Heroic also offers multiple customization options and an intuitive user interface that makes adding tables of contents to your site super easy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>4 pre-made table of contents styles to choose from</li><li>Collapsible table of contents</li><li>Mobile-friendly</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Heroic Table of Contents definitely stands out as one of the best WordPress tables of contents plugins you should consider for your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Price</strong>: Free</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/joli-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Joli Table Of Contents Plugin\">Joli Table Of Contents Plugin</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/joli-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"313\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-joli.png\" alt=\"Joli Table of Contents is an excellent option for those looking for a high-performing table of contents plugin\" class=\"wp-image-108528\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-joli.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-joli-300x134.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-joli-600x268.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/joli-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Joli Table Of Contents Plugin\">Joli Table of Contents</a> is an excellent option for those looking for a high-performing table of contents plugin. The plugin has features that prevent scripts and styles from loading when the table of contents is not displayed. This helps your pages load faster.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin also allows you to choose to add your table of contents automatically or manually using shortcodes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Choose between a hierarchical or flat view</li><li>Fully responsive</li><li>Multiple themes available</li><li>Customizable table of contents title alignment</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Above all, Joli Table of Contents is an SEO-friendly WordPress table of contents plugin that won&#8217;t slow down your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Price</strong>:  Free. Paid plans start at $29.99.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/luckywp-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"LuckyWP Table of Contents Plugin\">LuckyWP Table of Contents Plugin</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/luckywp-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-luckywp.png\" alt=\"LuckyWP Table of Contents is another excellent plugin you should consider when looking for the best WordPress table of contents plugins.\" class=\"wp-image-108541\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-luckywp.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-luckywp-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-luckywp-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/luckywp-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"LuckyWP Table of Contents Plugin\">LuckyWP Table of Contents</a> is another popular plugin you should consider when looking for the best WordPress table of contents plugins. The plugin makes it easy to add SEO-friendly tables of contents to your pages, posts, or custom post types. And because it&#8217;s compatible with almost all popular page builders, you can use it on any WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Auto or manual table of contents insertion</li><li>Control the number of headings to include in the table of contents</li><li>Option to no-index your table of contents</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>LuckyWP Table of Contents also allows you to choose from different color schemes, enabling you to create tables of contents that complement your theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Price</strong>: Free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cm-table-of-content/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"CM Table Of Contents\">CM Table Of Contents</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cm-table-of-content/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"313\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-cm-table-of-contents.png\" alt=\"CM Table Of Contents is another beginner-friendly WordPress table of contents plugin that makes generating a ToC on any page or post easy\" class=\"wp-image-108609\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-cm-table-of-contents.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-cm-table-of-contents-300x134.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-cm-table-of-contents-600x269.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cm-table-of-content/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"CM Table Of Contents\">CM Table Of Contents</a> is another beginner-friendly WordPress table of contents plugin that easily generates a table of contents on any page or blog post. However, despite being easy to use, the plugin is also feature-rich, especially when you opt for the paid version.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Define your table of contents by tags, classes, and ids</li><li>Different style options for the navigation table font size</li><li>Shortcodes for custom placement of the table of contents</li><li>Supports multilevel table of contents</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>CM Table of Contents is an excellent option for novice and expert WordPress users who want an easy way of adding tables of contents to their content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free plan available. Paid plans start at $29.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>8. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/simpletoc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"SimpleTOC\">SimpleTOC</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/simpletoc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"306\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-simple-toc.png\" alt=\"SimpleTOC is another easy-to-use table of contents plugin in the WordPress repository\" class=\"wp-image-108591\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-simple-toc.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-simple-toc-300x131.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-table-of-contents-plugin-simple-toc-600x262.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/simpletoc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"SimpleTOC\">SimpleTOC</a> is another easy-to-use table of contents plugin in the WordPress repository. Once installed, all you have to do is add a block and search for SimpleTOC in the block types. When you select SimpleTOC, the plugin automatically adds a table of contents to your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Lightweight and optimized code</li><li>Inherits your theme style</li><li>Native block support</li><li>Customizable table of contents heading</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for a simple, lightweight WordPress table of contents plugin with basic features, SimpleTOC could be it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p> <strong>Pricing</strong>: Free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Best WordPress Table of Contents Plugin: Our Expert Pick</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for the best WordPress table of contents plugin, then <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is definitely the best option. It&#8217;s super easy to use, has a robust feature set, and has unbeatable support.  The best part is you don&#8217;t have to add a dedicated table of contents plugin if you have AIOSEO installed. This will help you keep your plugin count to a minimum, resulting in <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/abc-of-wordpress-site-maintenance/\" title=\"8 WordPress Website Maintenance Tips for Improved Site Performance\">better site performance</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re on a tight budget and are looking for the best free WordPress table of contents plugin, then we highly recommend <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/easy-table-of-contents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Easy Table of Contents</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you pick the right WordPress table of contents plugin for your site. Once you’re done setting up your table of contents plugin, you may also want to see our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\" title=\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\">how to add an FAQ section in WordPress</a>, and see our expert pick of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress/\" title=\"8 Best SEO Plugins for WordPress in 2022 (Tried and Tested)\">the best SEO plugins</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-table-of-contents-plugins-for-wordpress/\">8 Best Table of Contents Plugins for WordPress for 2022</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://aioseo.com/best-table-of-contents-plugins-for-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"7 Best WordPress FAQ Plugins in 2022\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:116:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-faq-plugins/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=best-wordpress-faq-plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-faq-plugins/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 04 Aug 2022 12:39:07 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"Adding FAQs to WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"best WordPress FAQ plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"FAQ plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=107443\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:417:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress FAQ plugins? FAQ sections and pages help you improve the overall user experience, and they can also boost SEO by helping you land the featured snippet. Unfortunately, as powerful as WordPress is, it&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-faq-plugins/\">7 Best WordPress FAQ Plugins in 2022</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19332:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress FAQ plugins?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>FAQ sections and pages help you improve the overall user experience, and they can also boost SEO by helping you land the featured snippet. Unfortunately, as powerful as WordPress is, it doesn&#8217;t come with an FAQ option by default.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll share our expert picks of the best WordPress FAQ plugins to help you easily add FAQ sections to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What are FAQ plugins (And Why Are They Important for SEO)?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>FAQ plugins are specialized plugins built to make it easy to place FAQ sections on pages or blog posts. While you can add an FAQ section using the default content block in WordPress, those methods are not properly SEO optimized.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>FAQ plugins take out the hard work of <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\" title=\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\">adding FAQ sections</a> and save you time.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Why Are FAQs Important for SEO?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>FAQs are questions that many readers have about a particular topic or service. Addressing these topics makes it easy for your users to find the answers they&#8217;re looking for. It also helps you handle common objections they may have before purchasing your product. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding FAQs on your site can help boost your SEO rankings for a few reasons. First, it helps you improve search intent for users and search engines. As a result, your content ranks better in search.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another reason FAQS are important for SEO is that they can help you rank for the featured snippet, especially if your site outputs proper <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-faq-schema-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add FAQ Schema in WordPress [The Easiest Way]\">FAQ schema markup</a> for that page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Recently, search engines are giving a lot of prominence to sites with FAQ schema, and those websites get rich snippets that increase clicks and overall organic traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"474\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps.png\" alt=\"FAQs help you get rich results on search engine results pages.\" class=\"wp-image-105091\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps-300x203.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps-600x406.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know what FAQ plugins are and why you need them, let&#8217;s quickly dive into our expert picks.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>7 Best WordPress FAQ Plugins to Know</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing an FAQ plugin for your site can be challenging as there are thousands of them on the market. To help make it easier for you, we&#8217;ve carefully curated a list of FAQ plugins we know are reliable and easy to use.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best WordPress FAQ plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" title=\"AIOSEO - WordPress SEO Plugin\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) is a powerful WordPress SEO plugin and toolkit. It&#8217;s used by over 3 million websites to improve SEO rankings and increase site traffic. The plugin boasts many powerful features, including advanced SEO modules, sitemap generator, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/adding-a-table-of-contents-to-your-site-using-all-in-one-seo/\" title=\"Adding a Table of Contents to Your Site Using All in One SEO\">table of contents block</a>, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/internal-link-assistant/\" title=\"Link Assistant\">Link Assistant</a>, and many more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Aside from those powerful SEO features, AIOSEO also comes with a FAQ block with proper schema support. This means when you add FAQs using the AIOSEO FAQ block, it will properly output the FAQ schema in JSON format to help your site rank higher. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>All of this happens without any coding work required on your end.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can either create a new FAQ page or add FAQ sections to existing blog posts or pages to outrank your competitors.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"254\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2.png\" alt=\"Enter your questions and answers in the fields provided.\" class=\"wp-image-106787\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2-300x109.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2-600x218.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ block also enables you to hide entire FAQ sections or individual FAQs while still outputting the FAQ schema. This means you can hide the FAQs on the front end of your site, but still have them show up on search engine results pages (SERPs).</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Customization options</li><li>Automatically outputs JSON schema markup</li><li>Built with SEO in mind</li><li>Translation ready</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The biggest advantage of using AIOSEO&#8217;s FAQ block is that once you&#8217;ve <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">installed AIOSEO</a>, you don&#8217;t need another plugin to be able to add FAQs to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $49 for an annual plan of the SEO plugin. A free version is also available.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/heroic-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Heroic WordPress FAQ Plugin\">Heroic WordPress FAQ Plugin</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/heroic-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"327\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-heroic.png\" alt=\"Heroic WordPress FAQ is another top contender for the best WordPress FAQ plugin.\" class=\"wp-image-107586\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-heroic.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-heroic-300x140.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-heroic-600x280.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/heroic-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Heroic WordPress FAQ Plugin\">Heroic WordPress FAQ</a> is another plugin you should consider for adding FAQs to your site. Because it&#8217;s a no-code plugin, it&#8217;s super easy to use. With the Heroic WordPress FAQ plugin, you can create custom FAQ sections for your blog posts in a few minutes using the plugin&#8217;s drag-and-drop builder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Intuitive interface</li><li>Visual editor</li><li>Responsive</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Another big advantage of Heroic is that, unlike many FAQ plugins, it supports images, videos, and animations. These can be helpful when explaining difficult concepts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $49 for an annual license. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/tribulant/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Tribulant WordPress FAQ Plugin\">Tribulant WordPress FAQ Plugin</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/tribulant/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"240\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-tribulant.png\" alt=\"Check out Tribulant WordPress FAQ as you look for bthe best WordPress FAQ plugins.\" class=\"wp-image-107592\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-tribulant.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-tribulant-300x103.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-tribulant-600x206.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/tribulant/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Tribulant WordPress FAQ Plugin\">Tribulant WordPress FAQ</a> is a fantastic plugin with a full-featured administrative dashboard that allows you to manage your FAQs easily. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>A handy feature you&#8217;ll love is that Tribulant WordPress FAQ gives you the option to collect user FAQs via a form. You can choose to auto-approve the questions or manually go through them to select the ones you want to feature on your site. This helps ensure that your FAQ sections answer your users&#8217; exact queries.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>User search form</li><li>Dashboard widget</li><li>Multilingual</li><li>Accordion slider</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tribulant WordPress FAQ plugin should be high on your list for an FAQ plugin that gives you total control over how you handle FAQs on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $34/year. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/web10-faq-plugin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"FAQ by 10Web\">FAQ by 10Web</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/web10-faq-plugin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"487\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-faq-wd.png\" alt=\"FAQ WD by 10Web is an amazing FAQ plugin you should consider as you shop around for the best WordPress FAQ plugins. \" class=\"wp-image-107673\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-faq-wd.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-faq-wd-300x209.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-faq-wd-600x417.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/web10-faq-plugin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"FAQ by 10Web\">FAQ by 10Web</a> is an amazing FAQ plugin you should definitely check out as you shop around for the best WordPress FAQ plugins. It’s feature-rich and SEO friendly, ensuring you get the most mileage out of your FAQ sections.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An interesting feature that makes this FAQ plugin stand out is that it allows you to categorize your FAQs. This makes it easier for your visitors to find them quickly. FAQ by 10Web also gives you the flexibility to allow users to add comments as well as share your FAQs on social media.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Responsive and mobile-friendly</li><li>Display FAQs in an accordion view</li><li>Add author and category tags to each FAQ</li><li>Theme library for easy customization</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Add to all this the ease of use and FAQ by 10Web easily ranks as one of the best WordPress FAQ plugins on the market.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: $85 for a bundle of WordPress plugins + lifetime usage on all of them.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>5. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ultimate-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Ultimate FAQ\">Ultimate FAQ</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ultimate-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"308\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-ultimate-faq.png\" alt=\"Ultimate FAQ is another top contender that deserves to be on any list of the best WordPress FAQ plugins. \" class=\"wp-image-107675\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-ultimate-faq.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-ultimate-faq-300x132.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-ultimate-faq-600x264.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ultimate-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Ultimate FAQ\">Ultimate FAQ</a> is another top contender that deserves to be on any list of the best WordPress FAQ plugins because creating custom FAQ sections is super easy with this plugin. You can also add unlimited tags and categories to help users quickly find the answers they&#8217;re looking for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One nifty trick the Ultimate FAQ plugin has is enabling users to download your questions and answers in PDF format.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Bulk import FAQs from a spreadsheet</li><li>Customize your FAQs with CSS</li><li>Responsive accordion layout</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Ultimate FAQ comes with a powerful free version that can help you easily add an FAQ section to your site or pages in a few minutes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts at $67 for a single site license.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>6. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/helpie-faq/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Helpie FAQ\">Helpie FAQ</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/helpie-faq/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"324\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-helpie-faq.png\" alt=\"Helpie FAQ is another powerful WordPress FAQ plugin that can help you create FAQ sections on your site effortlessly\" class=\"wp-image-107678\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-helpie-faq.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-helpie-faq-300x139.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-helpie-faq-600x278.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/helpie-faq/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Helpie FAQ\">Helpie FAQ</a> is another powerful WordPress FAQ plugin that can help you create FAQ sections on your site effortlessly. The plugin allows for tags and categories to be added to your FAQs. You can then group your FAQs according to the assigned tags and categories, making it easy for visitors to find the information they&#8217;re looking for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Automatically adds FAQ schema</li><li>WooCommerce and Elementor integration</li><li>Basic FAQ shortcode builder</li><li>Responsive accordion layout</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Helpie FAQ is a simple yet effective FAQ plugin, making it worth a place on any best WordPress FAQ plugins list.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: $38.99 for an annual single-site license.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>7. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/quick-and-easy-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Quick and Easy FAQs\">Quick and Easy FAQs</a></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/quick-and-easy-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"314\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-quick-and-easy-faqs.png\" alt=\"Quick and Easy FAQs is one of the best free WordPress FAQ plugins on the WordPress repository. \" class=\"wp-image-107710\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-quick-and-easy-faqs.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-quick-and-easy-faqs-300x135.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/best-wordpress-faq-plugins-quick-and-easy-faqs-600x269.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/quick-and-easy-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Quick and Easy FAQs\">Quick and Easy FAQs</a> is one of the best free WordPress FAQ plugins on the WordPress repository. As the name suggests, the plugin makes adding FAQs on your site super easy.  For example, it allows you to add FAQs using a custom post type. These FAQs can then be added to pages or blog posts using shortcodes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Display FAQs in filterable groups</li><li>Easy FAQ section customization</li><li>Translation ready</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>For a free plugin, Quick and Easy FAQs packs quite a punch. However, it still lacks some advanced features. The developers are also inconsistent in rolling out updates.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Price</strong>: Free.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Best WordPress FAQ Plugin: Our Expert Pick</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Undoubtedly, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO</a> is the best FAQ plugin thanks to its ease of use, advanced features, and reliable support. Also, with AIOSEO, you don&#8217;t have to add any extra plugins, keeping your site lean and fast. It also saves you the extra cost of purchasing another plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you&#8217;re looking for the best free WordPress FAQ plugin, <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/quick-and-easy-faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"Quick and Easy\">Quick and Easy FAQs</a> would be it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you pick the right WordPress FAQ plugin for your site. Once you’re done setting up your FAQ, you may also want to check out our articles on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)\">how to add a table of contents</a><strong> </strong>to your blog posts, and our tutorial on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/\" title=\"How to Properly Set Up SEO for Different Languages and Countries\">setting up multilingual SEO</a> quite helpful.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-faq-plugins/\">7 Best WordPress FAQ Plugins in 2022</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-faq-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:156:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 01 Aug 2022 13:40:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"creating table of contents in WordPrerss\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"rich snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"Table of Contents block\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=106939\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:464:\"<p>Do you want to know how to create a table of contents in WordPress? Creating a table of contents (ToC) in WordPress can be tricky if you&#8217;re a beginner. Even if you&#8217;re an expert, using WordPress&#8217; default method can rob&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\">How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16012:\"<p>Do you want to know how to create a table of contents in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating a table of contents (ToC) in WordPress can be tricky if you&#8217;re a beginner. Even if you&#8217;re an expert, using WordPress&#8217; default method can rob you of a few precious minutes you could spend doing other productive things.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to automatically create a table of contents in WordPress and easily customize it to save you time.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-is-a-table-of-contents-important-in-wordpress\">Why is a Table of Contents Important in WordPress?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A table of contents helps users easily navigate your post, enhancing the user experience (UX). Most readers simply want to jump to the section with the answer they&#8217;re looking for, and a Table of Content helps them do that.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another benefit of a table of contents is that it helps you drive up your clickthrough rates (CTR) in SEO. Articles with a table of contents are more engaging and interactive on search engine results pages (SERPs) because they are enhanced by jump links.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to create a table of contents is important as it has many SEO benefits.\" class=\"wp-image-105094\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-300x126.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-serps-600x252.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Jump links are an excellent way to encourage visitors to click on your website and go straight to the section they’re most interested in. The high CTR signals to search engines that users find your content valuable, and as a result, your SEO rankings improve.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another advantage of tables of contents is that they can help you land the coveted featured snippet to get you maximum SEO traffic. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"449\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-featured-snippet.png\" alt=\"A table of contents can help you land the featured snippet.\" class=\"wp-image-106963\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-featured-snippet.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-featured-snippet-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-featured-snippet-600x385.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engines often pull listicle-based snippets of content to display as the featured snippet. The main reason is that lists (like tables of contents) and bullet points can clearly and concisely communicate answers to users&#8217; questions. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress\">How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The biggest challenge with creating a table of contents in WordPress is that it can take a lot of time to manually add jump links.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Luckily, there is a way that allows you to automatically add a table of contents in WordPress and even customize the headings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this tutorial, we will cover both methods on how to automatically create a table of contents in WordPress using a plugin as well as how to manually create a table of contents using code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, let&#8217;s jump right in.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-using-a-toc-block\">Method 1: How to Automatically Create a Table of Contents in WordPress</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to automatically create a table of contents in WordPress is by using the Table of Contents feature in All in One SEO plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" title=\"AIOSEO - WordPress SEO Plugin\">AIOSEO</a> is one of the best WordPress SEO plugins in the market, used by over 3 million website owners. Aside from dozens of powerful SEO features, it also comes with an advanced Table of Contents block that lets you automatically create a table of contents in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best SEO plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you need to do is install and activate the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">AIOSEO Pro</a> plugin. For detailed instructions, please see our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">step-by-step guide to installing AIOSEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have installed and set up the plugin, you&#8217;re now ready to add a table of contents in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Add the AIOSEO -Table of Contents Block</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To add a table of contents to your blog post, all you have to do is open the WordPress content editor and then click the <strong>Add block</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to select the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; Table of Contents</strong> block:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"498\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block.png\" alt=\"To add a ToC using a table of contents block, click the Add block button and select the AIOSEO - Table of Contents block.\" class=\"wp-image-107256\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-300x213.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-600x427.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you click on the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; Table of Contents block</strong>, it will automatically create a table of contents block with all your subheadings.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"395\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png\" alt=\"The Table of Content blocks helps you automatically create a table of contents on your posts.\" class=\"wp-image-104817\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/table-of-contents-block-1-600x339.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: How to Customize Your Table of Contents  </h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Not only does the Table of Contents block saves you time by automatically generating a table of contents, but it also has powerful customization features. For example, you can:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Customize the heading text in the table of contents</li><li>Choose to hide and re-order headings inside the Table of Contents block</li><li>Customize the table of contents anchors</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>To customize your table of contents, you need to click on the block&#8217;s options menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"701\" height=\"398\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-2.png\" alt=\"You can customize your table of contents using the block settings. \" class=\"wp-image-107345\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-2.png 701w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-2-300x170.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-2-600x341.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>From here, you can choose to reorder items in the table of contents or hide certain items.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll find other Table of Contents block customization options in the editor&#8217;s sidebar:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"362\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-3.png\" alt=\"You can also customize your ToC by using the block options in the sidebar.\" class=\"wp-image-107347\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-3.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-3-300x155.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-toc-block-3-600x310.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Here, you can change the list style and other advanced design settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done customizing your table of contents, make sure to save your draft, and that&#8217;s it! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Congrats, you&#8217;ve successfully added a table of contents in WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"create-toc-manually\">Method 2: How to Manually Create a Table of Contents in WordPress </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you don&#8217;t want to use a table of contents plugin in WordPress, then you can also manually create a table of contents in WordPress. However, the process can be very time-consuming.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at the manual steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Create HTML Anchors</h4>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"create-toc-manually\">The first step is to add HTML anchors to your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/\" title=\"Everything You Need to Know about Header Tags and How to Use them for SEO\">header tags</a> or subheadings. These HTML anchors will serve as internal links that you&#8217;ll use to link your various content subheadings in your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"create-toc-manually\">To get started, click on any subheading in the content editor. </p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"create-toc-manually\">Next, go to the <strong>Block</strong> settings in the sidebar and scroll down to the <strong>Advanced</strong> section. Then, type in your tag in the <strong>HTML anchor</strong> field.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"338\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-html-anchors-1.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to create a table of contents in WordPress involves adding HTML anchors to your heading tags.\" class=\"wp-image-108375\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-html-anchors-1.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-html-anchors-1-300x145.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-html-anchors-1-600x290.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Your HTML anchor should be similar to your subheading. This will help you remember the HTML anchor associated with each subheading.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: Create a Table of Contents Using a Regular Content Block</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve created your HTML anchors, you can now create your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, add a <strong>Paragraph</strong> block where you want to display your table of contents and title it accordingly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, add a <strong>List</strong> block where you&#8217;ll list all your subheadings. You can either type them out or copy and paste them.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"235\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-list.png\" alt=\"Create a table of contents by adding a paragraph entitled &quot;Table of Contents&quot; and then list your subheads under it.\" class=\"wp-image-108360\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-list.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-list-300x101.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-table-of-contents-in-wordpress-manually-list-600x202.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>This will serve as your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 3: Link Your Sub-headings inside the Table of Contents </h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done creating your table of contents listing, the next step is to link it to your subheadings using the HTML anchors you created.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To do that, highlight a list item in the table of contents and click on the <strong>Link</strong> icon.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"479\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-manually-3.png\" alt=\"Type in the HTML anchor and make sure to precede it with a hashtag (#).\" class=\"wp-image-107251\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-manually-3.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-manually-3-300x205.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-toc-in-wordpress-manually-3-600x411.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, type in the HTML anchor corresponding to the subheading you&#8217;re linking to and make sure to precede it with a hashtag (#). Once done, click on the <strong>Enter</strong> icon (or hit <strong>Enter</strong> on your keyboard), and the HTML anchor will be added to your table of contents list.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Repeat the process for the rest of the items on your table of contents.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you&#8217;ll notice through the process, if your table of contents is long, then this can be quite time-consuming. That&#8217;s why we always recommend using our Table of Contents block. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you know how to add a table of contents in WordPress easily. Once you’re done, you may also want to check out some of our tutorials. A great example is our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\" title=\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\">how to add an FAQ section in WordPress</a>. You may also want to check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/link-building-guide/\" title=\"The Ultimate Link Building Guide You Need for 2022\">ultimate link building guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>  </p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/\">How to Create a Table of Contents in WordPress (2 Simple Methods)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-table-of-contents-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:176:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 28 Jul 2022 13:14:16 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"faq schema\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"FAQ section in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"rich snippets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=106698\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:460:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add an FAQ section in WordPress? FAQs are a powerful way to boost your search engine optimization. They enable you to get featured in Google&#8217;s &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; section as well as get&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\">How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14321:\"<p>Do you want to know how to add an FAQ section in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>FAQs are a powerful way to boost your search engine optimization. They enable you to get featured in Google&#8217;s &#8220;People Also Ask&#8221; section as well as get more prominent listings (rich snippets) in search engine results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to properly add an FAQ section in WordPress with FAQ schema output to boost your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why is an FAQ Section Important to Your SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Having an FAQ section in your content is crucial to your SEO and can help boost your SEO rankings. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One reason is that it helps improve user experience (UX) by providing users with answers to their questions. As a result, they stay longer on your site, signaling to search engines that your content is valuable. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another reason is that FAQs improve your visibility on SERPs, especially if they output JSON schema. This is because schema markup helps you get rich snippets that look more attractive than other search results. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the case of FAQ schema, it results in your search result looking bigger and more prominent than other results, as in the example below:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"474\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps.png\" alt=\"FAQs help you get rich results on search engine results pages.\" class=\"wp-image-105091\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps-300x203.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-serps-600x406.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Search results like this also help show users that your content has the answers they&#8217;re looking for, thereby increasing your clickthrough rates (CTR). This signals to search engines that users love your content. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Easy Ways)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding an FAQ section with proper schema markup in WordPress is pretty easy if you have a powerful WordPress SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why the first step in adding an FAQ section in WordPress should be to install AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best SEO plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"AIOSEO\">AIOSEO</a> is one of the best WordPress SEO plugins on the market and has been downloaded over 100 million times. Savvy marketers use the plugin to boost their search rankings and drive tons of traffic to their sites. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed instructions on installing AIOSEO, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">check out our installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let&#8217;s quickly look at two ways you can add an FAQ section in WordPress with AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Method 1: How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress Using an FAQ Block</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to add an FAQ section with proper FAQ schema is by using the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-aioseo-4-2-3-faq-and-table-of-contents-blocks-all-new-url-slug-monitor/\" title=\"Introducing AIOSEO 4.2.3 — FAQ and Table of Contents Blocks + All New URL Slug Monitor\">AIOSEO&#8217;s FAQ block</a>. This easy tool allows you to add an FAQ section to your content without going through the hoops of manually adding schema markup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use it to add an FAQ section on any page or blog post on your site, so you can get rich snippets in Google search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Add the AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ Block</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To add an FAQ section, simply add the <strong>AIOSEO &#8211; FAQ</strong> block in the WordPress content editor as you would any other block:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"515\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block.png\" alt=\"Knowing how to add an FAQ section in WordPress is easy with our FAQ block.\" class=\"wp-image-106777\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-300x221.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-600x442.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to add the frequently asked questions related to your content or web page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you add FAQs in this block, it will automatically create proper FAQ schema.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"254\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2.png\" alt=\"Add your questions and answers in the fields provided. The questions have an H3 tag by default.\" class=\"wp-image-106787\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2-300x109.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-2-600x218.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Go ahead and repeat this step for as many frequently asked questions that you would like to add to the post or page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: Customize Your FAQ Section (Optional)</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO&#8217;s FAQ block has design options to help you customize the block’s background, text color, font size, and heading styles.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To customize your FAQ section, go to the block settings in the sidebar and expand the <strong>FAQ Options</strong> panel. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"406\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options.png\" alt=\"You can customize the AIOSEO FAQ block any way you want.\" class=\"wp-image-105254\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/faq-block-options-600x348.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>From here, you can select your text and background colors, typography and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 4: Set Your Visibility Status </h4>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO&#8217;s FAQ block also allows you to hide the FAQ section (or select FAQs) on the front end of your site while still outputting the JSON schema markup. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, your FAQs are visible, so users can see them on the front end. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"259\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-visibility.png\" alt=\"You can choose to hide the FAQ section or parts of it on the front end by turning the Visibility toggle to the off position.\" class=\"wp-image-106788\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-visibility.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-visibility-300x111.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-faq-block-visibility-600x222.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>To hide your FAQ section, simply turn the <strong>Visibility</strong> toggle to the off position. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>While users may not be able to see your FAQs, search engines can still read the schema markup, resulting in you getting rich snippets.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that&#8217;s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You have successfully added an FAQ section to any WordPress post or page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Method 2: How to Create a Dedicated FAQ Page + Schema Markup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re running an <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-start-an-online-store/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"How to Start an Online Store\">online store</a> or a product website, then you may want to create a dedicated FAQ page on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO comes with built-in support for dedicated FAQ page schema as well as a way for you to manually add custom schema markup.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s how you can use it to create a FAQ page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 1: Create an FAQ Page in WordPress</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply open the WordPress block editor to create a New page and call it FAQs or Frequently Asked Questions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the block editor, you can add all the frequently asked questions that you would like to add by typing them out as regular content blocks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Depending on the structure of your content, you can add the appropriate <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/header-tags/\" title=\"Everything You Need to Know about Header Tags and How to Use them for SEO\">heading tag</a> (e.g., H3 or  H4) to the questions.   </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"333\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-107919\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-300x143.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-600x285.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The only drawback of this method is that you&#8217;ll also have to manually add the FAQ schema to the page. </p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Step 2: Add FAQ Schema</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To add FAQ schema to your page, scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO Settings</strong> and click on <strong>Schema</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"305\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress.png\" alt=\"You can manually add FAQ schema to your content by using AIOSEO\'s schema markup feature.\" class=\"wp-image-106705\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-300x131.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-600x261.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, set your schema type to <strong>Web Page</strong>, and then your <strong>Web Page Type</strong> to <strong>FAQ Page.</strong> Doing so will open a window where you can type in your questions and answers.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"440\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-2.png\" alt=\"Enter your questions and answers in the fields provided. Click on Add New to add another FAQ.\" class=\"wp-image-107920\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-2.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-2-300x189.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-content-block-2-600x377.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To add another FAQ, click on the <strong>Add New</strong> button. Repeat the process until you&#8217;ve added all your FAQs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once done, you can either save your draft or hit publish. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that&#8217;s it! You have manually added an FAQ section and FAQ schema to your article. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-faq-schema-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add FAQ Schema in WordPress [The Easiest Way]\">Check out this guide</a> for more detailed step-by-step instructions on how to use this method to add schema markup to your WordPress posts and pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you know how to add an FAQ block in WordPress easily. Once you’re done, you may also be interested in our other guides. For example, you may want to know how to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-social-media-profiles-to-your-wordpress-sites-schema/\" title=\"How to Add Social Media Profiles to Your WordPress Site’s Schema\">add social media profiles to your site&#8217;s schema</a>. Or perhaps you may be interested in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/\" title=\"A Complete Blog Post SEO Checklist to Boost Rankings\">blog post SEO checklist</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\">How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"How to Properly Set Up SEO for Different Languages and Countries\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:174:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 25 Jul 2022 13:22:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"international SEO\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"multilingual seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"SEO for different languages\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=105515\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:466:\"<p>Do you want to know how to properly set up SEO for different languages and countries? WordPress, by default, allows you to build your site in one of 180 languages. However, it doesn&#8217;t allow you to serve content in different&#8230;</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/\">How to Properly Set Up SEO for Different Languages and Countries</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15990:\"<p>Do you want to know how to properly set up SEO for different languages and countries?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress, by default, allows you to build your site in one of 180 languages. However, it doesn&#8217;t allow you to serve content in different languages. This makes it difficult to rank your content in the languages of your target regions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This article will show you how to set up your SEO for different languages properly. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>How to Properly Set Up SEO for Different Languages and Countries (The Easy Way)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Successfully implementing SEO for different languages and countries is important as it allows you to grow your business beyond your locale. And thanks to the internet, you can easily grow an international audience and generate revenue from across the globe.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But for that to happen, you need to rank your content well in different languages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s how you can easily set up your SEO for different languages.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Step 1: Install AIOSEO</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to setting up your international SEO is installing and activating <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO) on your WordPress website. AIOSEO is the best WordPress SEO plugin on the market. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO is one of the best SEO plugins on the market.\" class=\"wp-image-100113\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/aioseo-600x267.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The plugin boasts over 3 million downloads and is always getting new powerful SEO features added. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why many smart website owners rely on the plugin to help them boost their rankings and drive traffic to their sites. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>An example of the features you can expect include Link Assistant for automated internal linking, a powerful Redirection manager that makes it super easy to implement redirects, and many more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And when it comes to setting up SEO for different languages and countries, this is where AIOSEO outshines most other <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress/\" title=\"8 Best SEO Plugins for WordPress in 2022 (Tried and Tested)\">WordPress SEO plugins</a> on the market. One main reason for this is a feature called the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/localizing-aioseo-data-via-the-translations-api/\" title=\"Localizing AIOSEO Data via the Translations API\">Translation API</a>. This feature enables third-party translation plugins to hook into your AISEO data so they can properly translate your SEO data.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a crucial element to winning at multilingual SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed instructions on installing AIOSEO, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\" title=\"Installing All in One SEO Pro\">check out our installation guide</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The setup wizard will take you through all the steps you should take to configure your site&#8217;s general SEO settings. For example, the wizard will help you configure <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/setting-the-seo-for-your-home-page/\" title=\"Setting the SEO for Your Home Page\">your Homepage&#8217;s SEO</a>. This includes optimizing your <strong>Snippet Preview</strong>, <strong>Page Title</strong>, and <strong>Meta Description</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you can set up other aspects of your site&#8217;s SEO. For example, you can <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/configuring-the-schema-settings-in-all-in-one-seo/\" title=\"Configuring the Schema Settings in All in One SEO\">set up your site&#8217;s schema</a>. Schema markup enables search engines to understand better what your website is about. It also helps them show rich results of your pages on SERPs. You can do much more with AIOSEO to boost your SEO for different languages. Examples include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/how-to-create-an-xml-sitemap/\" title=\"How to Create an XML Sitemap\">Creating a sitemap</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-edit-a-robots-txt-file-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Easily Edit a Robots.txt File in WordPress (Step by Step)\">Optimizing your robots.txt file</a></li><li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-social-media-profiles-to-your-wordpress-sites-schema/\" title=\"How to Add Social Media Profiles to Your WordPress Site’s Schema\">Configure your social media settings</a></li><li>And more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, dominating the SERPs in different countries and languages becomes much easier. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Choose Languages and Countries to Target</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An important aspect of effectively <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/multilingual-seo-mistakes/\" title=\"5 Multilingual SEO Mistakes You Want to Avoid (+ Pro Setup Tips)\">setting up your multilingual SEO</a> is understanding where your international traffic comes from. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily find this out by using a tool like Google Analytics. To do that, head to <strong>Audience » Geo</strong>. Here, you will be presented with 2 options — <strong>Language</strong> and <strong>Location</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-google-analytics-geo-language-1.png\" alt=\"Use Google Analytics to find which international languages and locations to target.\" class=\"wp-image-105809\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-google-analytics-geo-language-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-google-analytics-geo-language-1-300x244.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-google-analytics-geo-language-1-600x488.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>We advise you to review both to get a better picture of the traffic you should target. Look at the column that gives you the percentages of the traffic from each source to guide you on the languages and locations to target. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Install a Multilingual Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To properly set up your SEO for different languages and countries, you must install a multilingual plugin. Multilingual plugins help you serve content in many different languages. You have 2 options when it comes to the type of multilingual plugin you can use:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Auto-translate plugins</strong>: These use AI tools like Google Translate to translate your content automatically. Examples include GTranslate and Lingotek.</li><li><strong>Manual Translation plugins</strong>: This allows you to control your translations manually. This results in higher-quality translations and better search engine optimization. Examples include <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wpml/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"WPML\">WPML</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/translatepress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"TranslatePress\">TranslatePress</a>, among others.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know the tools you need to properly set up a multilingual site&#8217;s SEO, we&#8217;ll show you an example of how to do so using AIOSEO and WPML. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Setting Up SEO for Different Languages Using AIOSEO and WPML</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve installed AIOSEO and your multilingual plugin of choice, you can now go ahead and set up your SEO for different languages and locations. In this case, we&#8217;ll use WPML as an example. One reason for this is that WPML integrates very easily with AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>4. Set Up Your Page&#8217;s SEO Settings Using AIOSEO </h4>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, edit your post or page. Then scroll down to the <strong>AIOSEO Settings » </strong> <strong>General</strong>. Under the <strong>General</strong> section, you can then set the SEO for the post or page. This includes elements like your post title, meta description, and keywords.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"478\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-seo-settings.png\" alt=\"To set up SEO for different languages, you must first configure your site\'s general SEO. \" class=\"wp-image-106141\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-seo-settings.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-seo-settings-300x205.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-seo-settings-600x410.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also set your Facebook and Twitter settings on the <strong>Social</strong> tab. These include the title, description, image source, video URL, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"454\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-social-settings-1.png\" alt=\"Configuring your social media settings is also a prerequisite to setting up your SEO for different languages.\" class=\"wp-image-106147\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-social-settings-1.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-social-settings-1-300x195.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-social-settings-1-600x390.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Configuring your social network settings helps you optimize for engagement and sharing. This will lead to more traffic to your site and a boost in SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>5. Set Up Your Multilingual Plugin (WPML)</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>After installing <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wpml/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"WPML\">WPML</a>, you need to set up the plugin. To get started, click on WPML in your WordPress dashboard, and WPML will walk you through the 7-step setup process.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"297\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/wpml-setup-1.png\" alt=\"To set up SEO for different languages, you need a multilingual plugin like WPML.\" class=\"wp-image-106003\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/wpml-setup-1.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/wpml-setup-1-300x127.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/wpml-setup-1-600x255.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done with the WPML setup process, you can continue setting up your site for multilingual SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>6. Translate Your Site and Its SEO Settings with WPML</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>With your AIOSEO and WPML general settings configured, you can now optimize your content for other languages and countries. You can do this for every page and post you create by heading to the editor&#8217;s sidebar and expanding the <strong>Language</strong> section.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"699\" height=\"227\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-wp-sidebar-0.png\" alt=\"You can set up the different languages of your post by expanding the Languages section in your post editor\'s sidebar.\" class=\"wp-image-106020\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-wp-sidebar-0.png 699w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-wp-sidebar-0-300x97.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-wp-sidebar-0-600x195.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 699px) 100vw, 699px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Scrolling down the language settings, you&#8217;ll find the <strong>Use WPML&#8217;s Translation Editor</strong> toggle. It will be set to <strong>On</strong> by default, meaning WPML will automatically take care of all your translations. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"368\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-wp-sidebar-toggle-1.png\" alt=\"Using WPML\'s translation editor is fast as the translations are automatic.\" class=\"wp-image-106034\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-wp-sidebar-toggle-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-wp-sidebar-toggle-1-300x158.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/setting-up-seo-in-different-languages-wp-sidebar-toggle-1-600x315.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Toggling WPML&#8217;s editor off allows you to translate your website manually. This includes your SEO attributes, social media settings, as well as page and article content.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img width=\"700\" height=\"266\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/wpml-advanced-translation-editor.jpeg\" alt=\"Toggling WPML\'s editor off allows you to translate your text manually.\" class=\"wp-image-106039\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/wpml-advanced-translation-editor.jpeg 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/wpml-advanced-translation-editor-300x114.jpeg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/wpml-advanced-translation-editor-600x228.jpeg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Repeat the process for all the languages you want to include if you do your translations manually. Otherwise, WPML will take care of everything if you auto-translate your site. Just make sure to double-check and make sure the translations are accurate. If not, you can edit the translations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done, click <strong>Finish</strong>, and that&#8217;s it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ve set up your SEO for different languages and countries.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you know how to set up your SEO for different languages and countries. Once you&#8217;ve implemented the steps in this tutorial, you may also want to check out our other guides. Some helpful examples include our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/a-complete-local-seo-checklist/\" title=\"A Complete Local SEO Checklist: 10 Tips to Improve Rankings\">local SEO checklist</a> and our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-delete-url-parameters-from-google-search-console/\" title=\"How to Delete URL Parameters from Google Search Console (The Easy Way)\">dealing with unnecessary URL parameters</a> in Google Search Console.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a>. You’ll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/76569804/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://m.facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/\">How to Properly Set Up SEO for Different Languages and Countries</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-seo-for-different-languages-and-countries/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\